Commentary: Anderson starts with a good-length ball, outside off. Marcus Harris leaves it alone.
BEAUTY! Movement early on for James Anderson! Length ball, around off and curling away late. Marcus Harris has a tentative poke at it but the ball goes past his outside edge.
Back of a length, on middle. Marcus Harris blocks it out.
A bit fuller this time, around off. Marcus Harris defends it to cover.
Good-length delivery, ouside off and going on with the angle. Marcus Harris shoulders arms to this one.
A maiden over to start the proceedings in this pink-ball Test! Length ball, way outside off. Marcus Harris does not offer any shot to this one.

A huge appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested! Broad comes 'round the wicket straightaway and hurls a length ball, around middle which angles in late. David Warner sits back and shoulders arms to this one. He gets hit high on his pad. Top start from Stuart Broad.
Length ball, down leg. David Warner misses his flick and Jos Buttler moves to his right behind the sticks to gather the ball.
Full ball, around off. David Warner pushes it back to the bowler.
Length ball, nipping back in from off. Warner blocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller in length, outside off. David Warner prods and drives it to cover. Cannot find the gap though. Warner was quick to pass on the message to Harris by a loud "NO".
Back-to-back maiden overs! This is a good-length ball, way outside off. David Warner sways away from the line of the ball. Australia yet to get off the mark.
BEATEN! Good-length delivery, around off and shaping away late. Marcus Harris looks to defend but the ball zips past his outside edge.
A bit fuller this time, outside off. Marcus Harris shoulders arms to it.
Short of a length, outside off. Marcus Harris lets it through to the keeper.
Shorter in length, outside off. Marcus Harris lets it be.
Back of a length, around off. Marcus Harris gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it out.
First runs on the board for Marcus Harris and Australia! Anderson hurls a full ball, on the pads. Harris flicks it past the mid on fielder and the batters take three runs.
Back of a length, nipping back in sharply from off. Marcus Harris looks to leave it but the ball jags back and hits him high on his pad.
Good-length ball, around leg. Marcus Harris looks to flick but misses and gets hit on his thigh pad.
A loud shout for LBW but the umpire says no! Good-length ball, around off and jagging back in late. Marcus Harris looks to block but gets an inside edge onto his pad.
Fuller in length, way outside off. Marcus Harris does not offer any shot to this one.
Back of a length, way outside off. Marcus Harris sways away from the line of the delivery.
Broad goes fuller this time, around off. Marcus Harris plays an on drive but finds James Anderson at mid on.
Good-length ball, around the fourth stump and moving away late. David Warner leaves it alone.
Short of a length, outside off and shaping away. David Warner lets it through to the keeper.
That is a peach of a delivery! Good-length ball, around off and curling away late. Warner stays back and looks to defend but the ball zips past his outside edge.
Back of a length, outside off. David Warner shoulders arms to this one.
On a length, around off. David Warner gets behind the line of the ball and defends it to cover.
Good-length delivery, outside off and shaping away late. David Warner leaves it alone watchfully.
Fuller in length, way outside off. Marcus Harris shoulders arms to this one.

NOT OUT! Marcus Harris survives! That is a good review from Harris! This was a full ball, around off and jagging back in sharply. Harris looks to block but he misses and gets rapped in front. Broad appeals and the umpire raises his finger. Harris opts for a review and the Hawk Eye suggests that the ball would have gone down leg so the on-field decision is overturned!
Full ball, outside off. Marcus Harris looks to drive but it goes off the inner half of the blade to mid-wicket.
Full ball, down leg. Marcus Harris misses his flick.
Length ball, around off. Marcus Harris looks for a booming drive but it goes off the inside half of the bat towards mid on.
NO BALL! Good-length ball, on off. Marcus Harris blocks it out. No ball called as Stuart Broad oversteps.
Good-length ball, around leg. Marcus Harris tucks it to square leg.
On a length, around middle. David Warner defends it out.
Short of a length, on off. David Warner sits back and pushes it to cover.
Back of a length, around off. David Warner covers the line of the delivery and blocks it.
Length ball, around off. David Warner looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes to the backward point region.
Length ball, angling in from middle. David Warner defends it watchfully.
BEATEN! Top delivery from the veteran! David Warner is yet to get off the mark! Good-length ball, around off and shaping away late. Warner looks to defend but the ball beats his outside edge.
Length ball, on off. Marcus Harris blocks it out.
On a length, nipping back in from off. Marcus Harris defends it to mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! What a catch from Jos Buttler behind the sticks! England get their breakthrough and they are delighted! Broad bangs it into the deck, around leg. Marcus Harris stays back and looks to hook it behind square on the leg side but he gets a feather and Jos Buttler behind the sticks dives full stretch to his right and takes a stunner! This is a much-deserved wicket for Stuart Broad and the English bowlers finally get their reward!
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Marnus Labuschagne is up and running! Full ball, angling in from middle. Marnus Labuschagne drives it past the mid on fielder and the batters take three runs.

NOT OUT! David Warner escapes! Good-length delivery, around off and angling in sharply. Warner looks to block but he misses and gets hit high on his pad. Stuart Broad appeals and the umpire says no. England opt for a review but the Hawk Eye suggests that the impact is umpire's call and the wickets is missing. The on-field decision remains!
Length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Fuller in length, way outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it through to the keeper.
A stifled appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved! This was a good-length ball, jagging back in from off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to leave it but the ball hits him high on his pad.
Fuller in length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne prods and drives it past the mid off fielder. The batters take three runs.

Finally, David Warner is off the blocks! Full ball, around off. Warner pushes it back to the bowler who half-stops it and the ball goes towards mid off. Warner scampers through for a single and gets off the mark on his 20th delivery.
Length ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne presses forward and defends it to cover.
Full ball, outside off. David Warner looks to drive but gets a thick inside edge to the leg side.
Back of a length, around the fourth stump channel. David Warner shoulders arms to this one.
Good-length ball, outside off. David Warner lets it through to the keeper.
Length ball, darted on the pads. David Warner misses his flick and gets hit high on his pads.
Fuller in length, outside off. David Warner drags it to mid on.
Woakes starts with a maiden over! A length ball, around off. David Warner defends it solidly towards cover.

A full-length ball, on the pads, Marnus Labuschagne clips it through mid-wicket. The batters take two comfortably. Marnus Labuschagne wanted the third run as well but Warner sent him back smartly, as the fielder was already on the ball.

Two more! If it was a direct hit, Marnus Labuschagne could've been in trouble. Fuller and on the pads, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to square leg. He calls for two, the fielder collects the ball and throws it at the keeper, who clips the bails. Marnus Labuschagne's dive saves him this time. The batters get two runs in the end.
Good-length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone for the keeper.
On a length, outside off. Lifts off the seam with some inward movement. Marnus Labuschagne moves back in time and leaves it for the keeper.
Length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out watchfully.
This one stays a little low. Touch fuller, around middle and leg. The ball stays low off the deck. Marnus Labuschagne gets some bat on it and digs it out.
Touch short, around middle and leg. David Warner blocks it back to the keeper.

NOT OUT! After several replays of the Hot Spot. The third umpire says, it was inconclusive, as they could not make a difference if it hit the pad or bat first. David Warner survives the review. A length ball, around leg, the ball straightens a bit. David Warner looks to defend it out but misses and gets hit on the pads. Chris Woakes appeals but the umpire is unmoved. The RTS shows that the pad is being hit, but it is inconclusive, as the bat is very close to the ball and the Hot Spot showed a small dot on the blade. Hence, the third umpire asks the umpire to stick to his original decision.
Outside off, left alone by Warner.
Back of a length, outside off. Warner leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good-length ball, outside off. David Warner shoulders his arms.
Fuller and on off. David Warner hangs back and defends it onto the pitch. Another maiden for Chris Woakes.
A length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it towards mid on.
A fuller length and on off. Marnus Labuschagne stands back and defends it to cover.
Ollie Robinson serves a length delivery, on the fourth stump line. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and shoulders his arms to it.
Back of a length, on top of off. Marnus Labuschagne stays inside the crease and defends it watchfully.
Good-length ball, around middle. Marnus Labuschagne squares up and defends it back towards the bowler, showing the full face of the bat.
A length ball, around middle and off, on the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne defends it towards short mid on. A maiden over for Ollie Robinson now.
Good length and on off. Warner stays back and defends it out solidly.
Back of a length, around off, shaping away from the left-hander. David Warner shoulders his arms.
A length ball, around middle and leg, nipping in off the deck. David Warner looks to defend it out but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! David Warner gets the first boundary of the game. Chris Woakes serves it short and outside off. David Warner rides the bounce and cuts it through covers for a boundary.
Length and on top of off. David Warner defends it on the front foot.
WIDE! A sharp bumper, on leg. David Warner ducks under it. The umpire signals a wide due to the height.
Outside off, left alone by Warner. 5 runs coming off the over.
Good-length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms to it. He is not dealing with any ball outside off.

" placeholder="Please insert here...">14.2: Ollie Robinson to Marnus Labuschagne, Brilliant leave by Marnus Labuschagne in the end. Length ball, pitching outside off. Marnus Labuschagne was ready to play at it, but the ball nips in a long way. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms and gets pinged above the pads. Missing the stumps clearly. No appeal and just "Ooohhs" and "Aahhss" from the slip cordon.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it solidly.
Short and on off. Marnus Labuschagne remains solid in his defense.
Fuller and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne drives it towards mid off.
Length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go to the keeper. Another great over by Ollie Robinson and another maiden for him.
Fuller, on the pads, David Warner flicks it to mid-wicket but straight to the fielder.
Full-length ball, around off. David Warner creams the drive towards cover. Dawid Malan gets low to his left and stops it brilliantly.
Touch short, outside off, Warner cuts it to backward point but Hameed does well to stop it.
Back of a length, outside off, David Warner shoulders his arms to it.
Fuller and on off. David Warner drives it towards cover but straight to the fielder.
Another maiden for Chris Woakes. On a length, around off. Warner helps it towards cover-point.
Back of a length, on the pads, Marnus Labuschagne stays back and flicks it to square leg.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone for the keeper.
Length ball, around off, nipping in off the deck. Marnus Labuschagne inside-edges it onto the pads as he looks to defend it out off the front foot.
A sharp bouncer, wide of off stump. Marnus Labuschagne ducks under this one.
Length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone for the keeper.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne gets across and blocks it out. Another maiden for England. It has been a good battle.
Stuart Broad serves a short ball, outside off. David Warner stays back and cuts it hard towards point. Haseeb Hameed is positioned well to collect the ball.
Much better this time from Stuart Broad! A length ball, on off. David Warner presses forward and blocks it back to the bowler.

NO BALL! Overpitched, around middle and leg. David Warner plays the on drive towards long on and the batters run three before the fielder cuts it out. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.
Some movement this time! Good-length ball, outside off. The ball nips away off the seam. Marnus Labuschagne misses his attempt to defend and the ball goes past the outside edge.
BEATEN! A fuller-length delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne prods and looks to drive it through cover. The ball goes through to the keeper.
Absolute beauty! Marnus Labuschagne gets beaten again. On a length, around off, nipping away. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend it out but the ball beats the outside edge.

Oh dear, Stuart Broad beats him again. Marnus Labuschagne needs to be a little careful now. Good-length ball, on the fourth stump line. Marnus Labuschagne comes across and looks to block it out and gets beaten yet again, as the ball zips past the outside edge. Stuart Broad did everything right here, but was unable to get the edge into play. Brilliant over by him.
Stokes starts with a full-length ball, on off. Warner digs it out watchfully.
Slightly short and outside off. Warner cuts it to point, but not in the gap.
A length ball, around off. Warner works it to the left of the gully fielder off the outer half. The fielder dives to his left and makes a half stop. The batters cross for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone for the keeper.
A length ball, on the body, Marnus Labuschagne hangs back and defends it to the leg side.
Just a single from this over! Nicely bowled by Stokes. A length ball, angled into the pads. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and blocks it towards short mid-wicket.
Touch fuller and around off. David Warner presses forward and blocks it onto the deck.
Full-length ball, on the stumps. David Warner blocks it out watchfully. David Warner hasn't been his normal aggressive, maybe it is becuase he knows his record against Stuart Broad.

FOUR! David Warner gets on the act now and gets his second boundary of the game. Fuller and on the pads. David Warner clips it through mid-wicket. Chris Woakes gives it a chase but the ball wins the race to the fence.
Short and on the fourth stump line. David Warner shoulders his arms at it.
Good-length ball, outside off. Some fly off the seam. David Warner is happy to not chase it.
Full and on leg, Warner tucks it to mid-wicket and scampers through for a single. 5 runs off it.
Banged into the deck, around leg. David Warner stays back and swivel-pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Wide! A bumper, way outside off and over the batter's head. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone. Wided!
NO BALL! Ben Stokes oversteps! Back of a length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out.
Short of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Stokes serves a back-of-a-length delivery, around middle. Marnus Labuschagne gets right back in his crease to defend this one out.
NO BALL! Banged into the deck, yet again around middle. Marnus Labuschagne ducks underneath watchfully. Stokes oversteps and the umpire signals a no ball.
Stokes comes 'round the wicket this time and hurls a good-length ball, on leg. Marnus Labuschagne tucks it to mid-wicket.
Short of a length, around middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to mid-wicket.
Stokes goes back to over the wicket and bowls it fuller this time, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
FOUR! Nicely done! Banged in short, around middle. David Warner anticipates the bumper, stays back and pulls it over the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary.
Length ball, on off. David Warner blocks it out.
Broad comes over the wicket and hurls a full ball, on off. David Warner blocks it off the front foot.
Good-length delivery, outside off. David Warner leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off. David Warner lets it through to the keeper.
Short ball, down leg. David Warner sways away from the line of the ball.
Banged into the deck, around middle. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out off the back foot.

FOUR! Just wide of the slip fielder! Banged into the deck, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and looks to ramp it over the slip cordon but he does not middle it and it goes past the diving first slip fielder and into the fence.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Short ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to block but he gets hit high on his bat.
NASTY! Stokes bangs it into the deck, around middle. Marnus Labuschagne gets into awkward tangle and decides to leave it in the end. He gets hit on his ribs.
Banged in short, around middle. Marnus Labuschagne ducks underneath.
Tossed up, outside off. David Warner drives it to wide of cover and collects a single.
Fuller in length, around middle. Marnus Labuschagne prods and drives it to wide of mid off for a brace.
Flatter ball, on middle. David Warner defends it off the front foot.
Flatter ball, on middle and turning away. David Warner looks to turn it to the leg side but he gets a leading edge which falls towards the point region.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. David Warner blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. David Warner looks to cut but he misses and the ball goes past his outside edge.
Another bumper, around middle. Marnus Labuschagne ducks well underneath.
Banged in short, around leg. Marnus Labuschagne swivels and pulls it along the ground to fine leg for a single.
A well-directed short ball, around middle. David Warner pulls it to square leg, on the bounce.
Play and a miss! A bouncer, outside off. David Warner looks for a pull shot but he fails to get any bat on it.
Shorter in length, outside off. David Warner lets it go through to the keeper.
Short of a length, around off. David Warner blocks it off the back foot towards cover and yells 'NOOO'. That will be Dinner on Day 1!
Anderson starts with a length ball, angling in from middle. Marnus Labuschagne prods and pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length, outside off and nipping away slightly. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms to it.
Short of a length, around middle. Marnus Labuschagne gets right behind in his crease and blocks it solidly towards mid on.
Good-length delivery, around leg. Marnus Labuschagne tucks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
A maiden over to start the second session! Good-length ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it onto the deck, off the back foot.
Length ball, around middle. David Warner turns it to wide of mid on and takes off for a single. James Anderson there does well to keep it to just one.
Good-length ball, just outside off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to cover off the front foot.
Length ball, way outside off and jagging back in late. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms to this one.
Good-length delivery, around off and shaping away a bit. Marnus Labuschagne looks to block off the front foot but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards backward point.
A bit fuller this time, around off and angling in late. Marnus Labuschagne gets behind the line of the ball to block it.
Back of a length, way outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it through to the keeper.
A stifled appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested! Good-length ball, on leg. David Warner misses his flick and gets hit high on his pad.
Back of a length, outside off. David Warner leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, angling in late from middle. David Warner looks to leave it but the ball hits him high on his thigh. A stifled appeal but the umpire shakes his head,
Good-length ball, outside off. David Warner lets it be.
FOUR! Nicely done! Length ball, outside off. David Warner prods and carves it past the cover fielder for a boundary.
Fuller in length, around off. David Warner defends it to the cover region.
Back of a length, outside off and nipping back in sharply. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone and the ball goes just above off pole. A good leave in the end!
Banged in short, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne ducks underneath watchfully.
Short of a length, well outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Good-length ball, just outside off and straightening just that little bit after pitching. Marnus Labuschagne does not offer any shot to it.
Leg bye! Length ball, darted on the pads. Marnus Labuschagne misses his nudge to the leg side and gets hit on his pad. The ball rolls away behind square on the leg side for a leg bye.
FOUR! Width on offer and David Warner pounces on it! This is shorter in length, way outside off. Warner stays back and cuts it past the backward point fielder for a boundary.
Length ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it off the front foot.
Top delivery! Length ball, angling in from outside off and straightening after landing. Marnus Labuschagne prods and looks to defend but the ball goes past his outside edge.
Short of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Good-length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it through to the keeper.
BEATEN! Another jaffa! This is a good-length ball, around off and curling away late. Marnus Labuschagne looks to block but the ball beats his outside edge and goes to the keeper.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone. This is Anderson's fifth maiden over of the innings!
A length ball, on middle. Warner defends it watchfully from his crease.
A length ball, on off. Warner defends it off the front foot towards the off side.
Back of a length, on off. Warner gets back and defends it to cover-point this time.
Back of a length, on off. Warner pushes it off the back foot to short cover.
On a length, on off. Warner defends it solidly off the back foot onto the turf.
BEATEN! A good-length delivery and around off. Warner looks to defend his from his crease but the ball seams away nicely to beat the outside edge of his blade.
On a length and around off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
A length ball and angling into off. Marnus Labuschagne defends this off the back foot towards the on side.
A good-length delivery and around off. Marnus Labuschagne defends this with soft hands and gets a thick edge to gully.
A length ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it off the back foot towards backward point and gets a single.
A length ball, on off. Warner defends it towards the off side from his crease.
A length ball and angling into middle. Warner turns it away towards the on side and calls NO.
A length ball, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne nudges it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends this off the back foot square on the off side.
Back of a length, on off. Defended off the back foot towards the on side.
A length ball, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends this off the front foot towards the on side.
FOUR! Just over the head of Stuart Broad at square leg! A short ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it aerially and just over the diving effort of Broad at square leg for a boundary.
A length ball, on middle. Defended off the front foot towards mid on.
A length ball, outside off. Warner lets it go.
Ohh..beaten! A good-length ball, around off. Warner pushes his bat at it but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade.
Back of a length, outside off. Warner pushes it off the back foot to deep point for a single.
A length ball, on off. Defended off the front foot onto the turf.
A length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it off the back foot back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on leg. Warner defends this off the back foot towards the on side.
A short ball from 'round the wicket and angling into leg. Warner pulls it to fine leg for a single.

DROPPED by Jos Buttler! A short ball, around leg. Marnus Labuschagne gets back and looks to pull but gets a glove on that one. The ball goes to the left of Jos Buttler and he dives but ends up dropping it. He took a spectacular catch early on but could not swallow this one.
Back of a length, on off. Defended off the back foot towards short leg.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne gets back and defends it towards the on side.
A short ball on middle to end the over. Marnus Labuschagne ducks under it.
FOUR! David Warner showing his intent against the spinner. Overpitched, around off. David Warner shimmies down the pitch and creams it through cover for a boundary.
Looped up, around off, Warner presses forward and defends it out.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Warner drives it through cover for a single.
Floated, down leg. Marnus Labuschagne misses his flick.
Flighted full and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne tucks it to the leg side.
Tossed up, around off, Marnus Labuschagne drives it towards mid off for a single. A good over for the hosts. 6 runs off it.
Back of a length, on the fourth stump line. Marnus Labuschagne gets behind the line and blocks it out.

A single now! Back of a length, on the body, Marnus Labuschagne stays back, hops and nudges it to square leg. He gets across for a single. Surely, he is finding it difficult to negotiate against Stokes and will be happy to go to the other end.
Stokes comes 'round the wicket for the left-hander. Short ball, around off. David Warner leans back and lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Back of a length, around middle and off. David Warner stands tall and pulls it to mid-wicket. Not in the gap though.
A sharp bouncer this time, outside off, this one flies off the deck. David Warner leaves it alone.
Slightly fuller but wide outside off, David Warner leaves it watchfully. Stokes has only one game-plan and that is to bowl short. England need to find some more ways to trouble the batters.
Way down leg, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Tossed up, full, around middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to square leg and gets across for a single.
Floated, full and on middle. David Warner prods and blocks it back to the bowler.
Up and over! Tossed up, full and on off. David Warner comes down the track and chips it over mid off. Ben Stokes gives it a chase and pulls the ball back in play and keeps it down to a brace.
Full and around off. David Warner drives it to sweeper cover for a single.
5 runs off it. Full, around middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to square leg for a single.
Slightly short, on the body. Marnus Labuschagne hops inside the crease and defends it to short leg off the inner half.
Short ball, around leg. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it towards short mid on.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne hops and blocks it out.
Stokes continues to bowl the short delivery. This time on off. Marnus Labuschagne hops yet again and blocks it out.
Silly mid on comes into the play now! Back of a length, going down leg, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Another short ball, sliding down leg. Marnus Labuschagne does not chase this one either.
Back of a length, around the hips. David Warner clips it through mid-wicket for a brace.
A single now! A length ball, around off. David Warner punches it towards point. Haseeb Hameed misfields which allows Warner to get to the other end.
A dot this time! Length ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it to cover.
Good-length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone for the keeper.
Fuller, on leg, Marnus Labuschagne nudges it towards square leg.
Good-length ball, outisde off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it sail past him and into the keeper's mitts.
FOUR! David Warner gets it away for a boundary! A short ball on middle. David Warner backs away and slaps it over extra-cover for a boundary.
A good short ball this time by Stokes on middle. Warner sways away from the line of the ball this time.
FOUR! Another boundary and another half-century for Warner! A short ball, on leg. Warner pulls it to deep backward square leg for a boundary. Another gritty knock by David Warner!
Back of a length, on middle. Warner defends this off the back foot towards the on side.
A short ball and down the leg side this time. Warner lets it go.
A short ball, around off. Warner lets it go this time.
A good-length delivery and around off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Back of a length and around off. The ball seams away a little after pitching and beats the outside edge of Marnus Labuschagne's blade as he looks to defend.
A length ball and angling into off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it to the on side.
On a length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.

A half-chance there! A length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to backward point and sets off for a single. David Warner is late to respond and then runs towards the danger end. There is a shy at the striker's end but the fielder misses. Warner is anyway inside his crease.
Back of a length, on off. Warner defends this off the back foot onto the turf.
Back of a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne gets across and defends it to short leg.
Back of a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne rides the bounce and defends it to the on side.
This time he pitches it up a little. Marnus Labuschagne defends this without much foot movement this time.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne is right back to defend this one.
Another shorter length delivery on off. Marnus Labuschagne gets back and defends it to mid-wicket.
Stokes bowls this from 'round the wicket and shorter around leg. Marnus Labuschagne works it to backward square leg for a single.
Length ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne prods and pushes it back to the bowler.
Thick edge found but safe! A length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend this off the fornt foot but gets a thick outside edge and just short of gully.
FOUR! Easy pickings! A full toss, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne just flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
A length ball, on off. Defended off the back foot.
Back of a length, on off. Solidly defended off the back foot again.
A good-length ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes forward to defends and gets a thick outside edge to backward point. The batters take a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Full ball, on middle. David Warner just lifts this over mid off but doesn't time it well. The fielder from mid off cuts it off and the batters run three. Good running.
A length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go.
On a length and angling into middle. Marnus Labuschagne works it to short mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends this off the back foot onto the turf.
A full ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it straight to mid off.
A good-length delivery and around off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go this time.
Full ball, outside off. David Warner stays back and drives it past the cover fielder. Haseeb Hameed there gives it a chase and slides in front of the ropes to keep it to three.
Good-length ball, angling in from middle. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out.
BEATEN! Top delivery from Woakes! A length delivery, around off and shaping away late after landing. Marnus Labuschagne looks to block but the ball zips past his outside edge.
Good-length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but it goes off the thick edge past the gully fielder for a brace. Australia bring up their 100!
Length ball, just outside off and going on with the angle. David Warner leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around off. David Warner gets behind the line of the ball and defends it to cover.
Overpitched ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne digs it out back to the bowler.

Sloppy from Haseeb Hameed at square leg. Full ball, darted on the pads. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it and Hameed at square leg does not stop the ball cleanly. The ball goes past him and the batters take three runs.
Length ball, down leg. David Warner misses his flick.
Good-length ball, angling in from middle. David Warner blocks it out.
Short of a length, outside off. David Warner shoulders arms to this one.
Broad bangs it into the deck, around middle. David Warner ducks underneath watchfully.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, jagging back in from off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it out.
Length ball, nipping back in from off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it through to the keeper.
A bit fuller this time, just outside off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it to cover.
Short of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off. David Warner stays back and punches it past the cover fielder for a couple of runs. That brings up the 100-run partnership between Warner and Labuschagne!
Full ball, outside off. David Warner drives but finds the mid off fielder.
Short of a length, around off. David Warner blocks it out.
Banged into the deck, around leg. David Warner swivels and pulls it to deep square leg for a run.
Banged into the deck, way outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Banged into the deck, around middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne rocks back, rides the bounce nicely and pulls it along the ground towards deep square leg for one.
A bumper, around off. Marnus Labuschagne gets behind the line of the ball to block it but it hits his glove and the ball pops out onto the deck.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
A well-directed bumper, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it in front of square past the diving mid-wicket fielder for a couple of runs.

Fuller in length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne presses forward and drives it past Ben Stokes at mid off. Stokes chases it and the batters take three runs. A round of applause in the crowd, as Marnus Labuschagne takes his tally to 2000 Test runs.
Shorter in length, around leg. David Warner tucks it to fine leg and the batters cross for a single.
Full ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms to this one.
Darted on the pads, David Warner clips it through mid-wicket for a single.
A couple now! Floated, around leg. Marnus Labuschagne gets low and sweeps it to fine leg. The batters collect a brace now.

Three runs this time! This one just goes past the leg slip. Floated, on the pads. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and looks to flick it towards fine leg. The ball goes off the shoulder of the blade and past Ben Stokes at leg slip. The batters take three before the fielder cuts it off.

Floated, full and around middle. David Warner looks to go for the reverse-sweep. The ball takes the shoulder of the blade and bounces to his left. It was going towards the stumps and Warner was worried, as he turns and looks to put it away but luckily for him the ball stops near the pole.
BEATEN! Some turn now, even Warner is surprised. Looped up, full, around off. The ball turns away and beats the outside edge as Warner presses forward to defend it out.
On off, defended out solidly.
Good length and on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it to cover.
BEATEN! A peach of a delivery. Good length and on off, nipping away. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend it out but gets beaten at the outside edge.

FIFTY for Marnus Labuschagne! He has delivered yet again in this series and would love to take it to three digits. Fuller and on off. Marnus Labuschagne leans forward and drives it through mid off. The batters take three runs.
Length and outside off, Warner leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full length and on off. David Warner punches it to point but straight to the fielder.
NO BALL! Angled into the pads, Warner clips it through square leg. The batters collect a brace. Ollie Robinson oversteps and the umpire signals a no ball.
Full and on off. Warner prods and defends it into the pitch.
Floated, full and on off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it through covers for a single.
Short and around off. Warner cuts it towards point for a single.
Tossed up, full and on off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it to cover but straight to the fielder.
Full and on leg, Marnus Labuschagne clips it to square leg for a single.
Short and on middle. David Warner pulls it to square leg for a single.
Quicker and short, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and blocks it out watchfully. That will be Tea on Day1!
Anderson starts from 'round the wicket. Length ball, on off. Warner defends it out solidly.
Full length and on off. Warner drives it to extra cover but straight to the fielder.
Good-length ball, angled into the batter. David Warner defends it to the leg side.
On a length, around off, Warner defends it back to the bowler with full face of the bat.
Good-length ball, outside off, nips in a bit late. Warner leaves it alone for the keeper.
A couple now! First runs of the final session. A length ball, outside off. David Warner punches it towards deep point. The batters collect a brace.
A length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne inside-edges it towards square leg for a brace.
Length and on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne shuffles across and clips it to the leg side.
Full-length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it towards mid on.
Another dot now! On a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne comes across and shoulders his arms to it.
Full and on off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it to extra cover. Cannot find the gap. Only 2 runs off it.
Good-length ball, outside off. David Warner prods and punches it to wide of the deep point fielder for a couple of runs.
Short of a length, around off. David Warner hangs back and blocks it.
Back of a length, around off. David Warner stays back and works it behind square on the off side for a run.
Another ball, shorter in length, just outside off. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and blocks it out.
Good-length delivery, angling in from outside off. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and defends it towards point.
Short of a length, way outside off. Marnus Labuschagne hangs back and leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
Good-length ball, outside off. David Warner lets it through to the keeper.

Top effort from Ben Stokes at mid off to save a certain boundary! Length ball, outside off. David Warner drives it back past the bowler. Stokes cuts it off by running to his left from mid off and saves a couple of runs for his side.
Another ball, fuller in length, outside off. David Warner drives it past the mid off fielder. Ben Stokes gives it a chase and the batters take three runs.
Back of a length, around leg. Marnus Labuschagne tucks it to square leg.
Length ball, angling in from off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it back past the bowler. It is Ben Stokes yet again who chases the ball and the batters take three more runs.
Length ball, outside off and curling away late. David Warner leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it out off the back foot.
Good-length delivery, around off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it to cover.
Short of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and blocks it out.
Short of a length, around middle. Marnus Labuschagne turns it to square leg.
Length ball, darted on the pads. Marnus Labuschagne nudges it to mid-wicket.
Another maiden over from Anderson! Back of a length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne hangs back and guides it to the slip cordon, on the bounce.
Short of a length, around middle and leg. David Warner tucks it to wide of mid on and takes a single. Marnus Labuschagne wanted the second run but was sent back by Warner.
Good-length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Banged in short, around off. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it in front of square and collects a run.
On a length, around off. David Warner prods and keeps it out.
A bit fuller this time, around off. David Warner presses forward and blocks it to cover.
Length ball, around off and shaping away late. David Warner presses forward to defend but it goes off the inner half of the blade towards mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery! Good-length ball, angling in from outside off and curling away late. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but the ball whistles past his outside edge.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne stays back, rides the bounce well and punches it past the cover region for a couple of runs.
Length ball, angling in from middle. Marnus Labuschagne presses forward and pushes it to mid on.
Fuller in length, just outside off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it straight back to the bowler. James Anderson does well to bend down and stop the ball.
Short of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it to wide of mid off but Ben Stokes there moves across quickly and prevents the single.
Just short of the mid off fielder! Length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to drive but the ball hits high on his bat and goes to Ben Stokes at mid off, on the bounce.
A length ball, on middle. Warner nudges it to square leg.
A full ball, on middle. Warner drives it past mid on. Ben Stokes running from mid off cuts it off and the batters run three.
A length ball, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but the ball hits his gloves as it takes off from a length.
A length delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Another length ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go again.
Good leave to end the over! A good-length delivery and around off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms to this one.
A length ball and angling into leg from 'round the wicket. David Warner looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads.
FOUR! A shorter length this time and punished! A short ball on middle. David Warner gets back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Warner lets it go.
Back of a length, outside off. Warner cuts it to deep point for a single.
Shorter length again on off. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it to square leg.
FOUR! Two boundaries in the over! A short ball again by James Anderson on off. Marnus Labuschagne stays deep in his crease and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
A bouncer, outside off. David Warner lets it go comfortably.
FOUR! A full ball this time and David Warner takes full advantage of it. A fuller ball, on off. David Warner drives it this time aerially over cover-point for a boundary.
Shorter length, around leg. Pulled to fine leg for just a single this time.
FOUR! Another boundary and Australia are getting a move on here! Back of a length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne backs away and smashes it through covers for another boundary.
Shorter length again, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne backs away and slaps it to mid on.
Back of a length, going down leg. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone for the keeper. 9 runs off it, Australia is starting to accelerate here.
Fuller on middle. Warner defends this off the front foot towards the on side.
Flatter and on leg this time. Warner tucks it to backward square leg for a single.
Fuller on middle. Marnus Labuschagne works it to square leg for another single.
Slower in the air on middle. Defended off the front foot.
Shorter length, on off. Pushed to covers for a single.
Fuller on leg. Worked to square leg.
FOUR! Just five needed now for a century! A short ball, on middle. David Warner pulls it aerially towards backward square leg for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Oh! David Warner is gone and misses out on another century! A short ball, outside off. David Warner cuts it hard but straight to Stuart Broad at covers. He takes a fine flat catch and David Warner has to walk back. David Warner is disappointed and he deserved a century after playing so well throughout the day. Stuart Broad was the only fielder there and David Warner finds him perfectly. This is the opening England needed and they would like to capitalise on it now.
Howout: c Stuart Broad b Ben Stokes

Commentary: A short ball, around off. Steven Smith pulls it to mid-wicket for a single.
Shorter length and around leg. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go.
A bouncer again and around leg. Marnus Labuschagne gets across and pulls it to fine leg for a single.
NO BALL!  A short ball, on off. Steven Smith ducks under it. Ben Stokes oversteps and the umpire calls it a No Ball.
A short ball to end the over on middle. Steven Smith ducks under it and end of a successful over from Ben Stokes.
Back of a length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne rides the bounce and pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Good-length ball, outside off, Smith looks to defend it out but misses.

Some sound but not off the blade. A length ball, around off. Smith comes across and looks to defend it out but misses. The ball goes off the top end of the pad and into the keepers mitt's. A stifled appeal by the bowler but the umpire shows no interest.
Full length and on middle. Steven Smith clips it to mid-wicket.
Smith gets squared up now. A length ball, around off. Smith looks to work it to the leg side. The ball takes the outer half and goes towards point.
Full-length and on off. Steven Smith gets slightly squared up this time. He defends it to the off side.

Back of a length, around middle. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and pulls it towards square leg for a couple. Marnus Labuschagne had to cover a lot of ground for the second run, as Ben Stokes was a wall standing in middle, on his way back.
FOUR! Top Shot! Marnus Labuschagne moves to 78 now. A short ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne rides the bounce well and smacks it through square leg for a boundary.

Just falls in front of the keeper. Marnus Labuschagne gets lucky this time. Stokes serves it back of a length, around middle and leg. He stays back, swivels and looks to pull it away. The ball comes in contact with the ball and deflects off his shoulders in front off the keeper, which is why all the pace goes off. Jos Buttler tries to charge in front of him, but all the English hope dies, as the ball lands on the ground.
Short and on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it towards square leg. The batters take two.
Good-length ball, outside off, nips in a bit. Steven Smith shoulders his arms to it.
A length ball, on off stump. Steven Smith blocks it out solidly.
Length and on off. Smith gets behind the line and blocks it out solidly.
On a length, on off. Steven Smith blocks it to point.
NO BALL! Full length and on off. The ball stays low after hitting the deck. Smith does well in the end to dig it out. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.
Fuller and on off, Smith defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Smith takes on the short ball and gets his first boundary of the innings. Back of a length, on off. Smith swivels on the back foot and pulls it through square leg for a boundary.
Marnus Labuschagne moves back to the leg side and Stokes follows the batsman with a length ball. Marnus Labuschagne defends it to the leg side.
FOUR! Short and punished! Short ball, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it through square leg for a boundary. The runs are coming in thick and fast for the hosts.
Back-of-a-length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to pull it away. The ball hits him on his elbow. That's nasty.
Short ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it behind square for a single.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Steven Smith ducks under it.
CLOSE! Back-of-a-length ball, on off. Steven Smith looks to block it away. The ball takes the inner half and falls just short of the short leg fielder. This was very close.
Length and around off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it out watchfully.
On a length, around off, some extra bounce this time off the deck. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend it out and does so with the outside edge.
Full length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it back to the bowler.
Full-length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it gently towards cover.

A loud appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. This got a lot of interest from Jos Buttler and Joe Root from behind the stumps, but as England only have a single review left now, the skipper opted against it. A length ball, around middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne prods and looks to defend it out but fails to get any bat on it. He gets pinged on his pads. The English players appeal but the umpire does not raise his finger.

Marnus Labuschagne now trying to cheer the bowler up. A length ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne presses forward and defends it out. As soon as he gets any bat on it. He says, "this is a good delivery". Ollie Robinson shares a smile with the batsman.
Flatter ball, turning down leg. Steven Smith leaves it alone.
Tossed up, on a length, around middle. Steven Smith blocks it out off the front foot.
Flatter ball, turning way down leg. Steven Smith does not offer any shot to this one.
Flatter ball, on a length, around leg. Steven Smith tucks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, around middle. Steven Smith defends it off the front foot.
Loopy ball, around middle. Steven Smith clears his front leg and whips it off his pads but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Full ball, darted on the pads. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to square leg.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Short of a length, just outside off. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and defends it to cover.
A bit shorter this time, well outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it through to the keeper.
Broad bangs it into the deck, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne does not offer any shot to this one as he sways away from the line of the ball.
Another bumper, around middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it in front of square towards deep square leg for a run.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne prods and blocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller in length, down leg. Marnus Labuschagne gets down on his knee and sweeps it to deep backward square leg for one. 200 comes up for Australia!
Flatter ball, turning down leg. Marnus Labuschagne tucks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
A bit shorter in length, around leg. Steven Smith nudges it to wide of square leg and collects a run.
Tossed up, around middle and leg. Steven Smith presses forward and turns it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball, on middle. Steven Smith turns it to mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne turns it to mid-wicket.
Short of a length, way outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it through to the keeper.
On a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone watchfully.
Back of a length, well outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Short of a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and blocks it out.
Tossed up, around leg. Steven Smith stays back and turns it to square leg for a single.
Flatter ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne rocks back and flat-bats it to cover.
Flatter ball, sliding down leg. Marnus Labuschagne tucks it to wide of square leg for one.
Shorter in length, turning down leg. Steven Smith works it with the turn behind square on the leg side for a single.
Fuller in length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it to wide of mid off and collects a run.
Flatter ball, turning sharply down leg. Steven Smith leaves it alone for the keeper to collect it.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it to square leg.
Good-length delivery and around off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne rides the bounce and defends it to the off side.
A fuller ball, on middle. Pushed to mid on.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it square on the off side.
On a length, on middle. Tucked behind square on the on side and comes back for two runs.
Quicker on middle. Defended off the back foot.
On middle and leg. Turned behind square on the on side for a single.
Drifting on the pads again. Nudged to square leg for a single.
Fuller on middle. Worked away to mid-wicket.
Shorter length on middle and leg. Smith gets back and tucks it behind square on the on side for a single.
A fuller ball, on leg. Turned to square leg.
BEATEN! Good-length ball, outside off. Smith steps a long way towards the line of the delivery and gets squared up. The ball zips past the outside edge.
A full ball, on middle. Smith pushes it off the front foot towards mid on.
Back of a length, on off. Smith gets back and defends it to the on side.
Good-length delivery on off. Steven Smith gets forward and blocks it towards the off side.
A length ball, on off. Smith works it to short mid-wicket comfortably.
Back of a length, on off. Smith looks to work it away towards the on side. Gets a leading edge square on the off side.
Fuller ball, on middle. Defended off the fornt foot towards the on side.
A fuller ball, on off. Driven to covers for a single.
A flatter ball, on off. Smith gets back and defends it.
A shorter length delivery on middle. Smith gets back and blocks it.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Smith works it to the on side.
On middle and leg. Smith nudges it to the on side again.
Back of a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out off the back foot.
A length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go.
A good-length delivery and around off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone again.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends this watchfully onto the turf off the back foot.
On a length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone again.
BEATEN! A beauty by Chris Woakes! A good-length delivery and around off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend it but the ball seams away sharply to beat the outside edge of his blade.
On a length, on off. Steven Smith moves across and defends it to the on side. Not much swing on that first ball.
A good-length delivery and around off. This time a little swing as it swings in to the batter. Steven Smith leaves it alone comfortably.
Good-length ball, outside off, moving away. Steven Smith does not chase it at all.
Nice movement! Good sign now. A full-length ball, around off. The ball shapes away after hitting the deck. Smith lets it go to the keeper.
Good-length ball, outside off. The ball nips in a long way. Smith hops and looks to push it through cover. He gets an inside-edge onto the pads.
Seventh maiden of the game for James Anderson! A length ball, on the fourth stump line. Steven Smith gets behind the line and defends it onto the deck.

OUCH!! That must've hurt Marnus Labuschagne. A length ball, around off. This time the ball nips in off the deck. Marnus Labuschagne gets squared up, as he looks to defend it out. He gets hit on his elbow. This is going to hurt.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone for the keeper.

JAFFA! Marnus Labuschagne is not shy of appreciating such great deliveries. Good-length ball, outside off, the ball holds its line after hitting the deck. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend it out but misses.
Another one beats the outside edge! A length ball, outside off, Marnus Labuschagne comes forward and looks to drive it away but misses and the ball beats the outside edge.
A length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne finally gets his bat to the ball and blocks it out.
Fuller and on off. Nips in a bit. Marnus Labuschagne blocks out solidly.
Length ball, going down leg. Smith leaves it alone for the keeper.
Touch short and outside off, Smith shoulders his arms to it.
James Anderson fires in a full-length ball, around middle and leg. Steven Smith moves across and defends it to the leg side.
Slightly short, on off. Smith gets across and nudges it to the square leg.
Full length, on middle and leg. Smith gets inside the line and tucks it to short leg.
Another maiden for James Anderson. England are still hunting for the nick. Anderson wastes an opportunity this time, as he serves a length ball, down leg. Smith is happy to leave it alone.
Full-length ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend it out. The ball takes the inside edge and goes towards fine leg. The batters cross for a single. Marnus Labuschagne moves to 95.
Good-length ball, outside off, moving away. Steven Smith lets it go to the keeper.
Length ball, sliding down leg. Steven Smith looks to flick it away but misses. Jos Buttler dives to his left to make the stop.
Back of a length, outside off. Smith shoulders his arms.
FOUR! Nicely played, well timed by the skipper. Full-length ball, outside off. Steven Smith leans forward and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball, on off. Smith blocks it out solidly. 5 runs coming off it and there were no signs of getting the edge into play.
A full-length ball, around middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne defends it to the leg side.
Outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it to cover off the front foot.

DROPPED! Hard to say who is more tired. Labuschagne? Because there was barely any feet movement. That was a very poor shot. Or Buttler? He would have taken that catch 999 times out of 1000. But tonight was that 1 odd time where he just could not catch this dolly! Either ways, poor Jimmy has to bear the brunt of bad luck. This is the second time he has dropped Marnus Labuschagne. A regulation catch goes down and with the all the English heads go down as well. Good-length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to drive it through the cover region. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the right of the keeper. Jos Buttler gets towards the ball but is unable to pouch it comfortably. And what about Marcus Harris? He will be sitting there in that Aussie dressing room and wondering - 'Well, Jos dropped a tough one of Marnus early on and now a dolly of the same guy. Then why did he have to take a jaffa of mine?'
Length ball, down leg. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Good length and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone for the keeper and this time Jos Buttler gets a hold of it.
Ollie Robinson starts with a one down the leg side. Steven Smith lets it go.
A full ball, on off. Smith gets forward and defends it.
A full ball, on off. Smith punches this down the gorund, The fielder running behind it cuts it off and the batters run three.
Oh...swing and bounce there! A good-length delivery and around off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend it but the ball moves away sharply to beat the outside edge of his blade.
A good-length delivery, around off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone this time.
On a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go again. England are still searching for that wicket with the new ball.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Steven Smith gets across and leaves it alone. The ball bounces over the stumps and goes back to the keeper.
A length ball, on off. Smith defends this with soft hands square on the off side and gets a quick single.
A length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone with his typical unusual style.
A length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it square on the off side this time off the back foot.
A length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go comfortably.
Another length ball, outside off and Marnus Labuschagne lets it go comfortably again.
A good-length delivery and around off. Smith just shoulders his arms and lets it go. They need to make batters play here!
A length ball, outside off. Smith decides to let it go again.
On a length and seaming into the batter. But Steven Smith leaves it again. Good leave.
Ollie Robinson tries to bowl it on the stumps and ends up drifting down the leg side. Smith leaves it alone.
A full ball and down the leg side again. Smith looks to clip it but misses.
A length ball, outside off. Steven Smith lets it go again. Easy leave for Steven Smith.
A good-length delivery, outside off and jagging in sharply. Marnus Labuschagne is in no mood to play that one and shoulders his arms again.
Beaten this time! Good-length delivery and around off. Marnus Labuschagne tries to defend it off the front foot but gets beaten as the ball misses the outside edge of his blade.
A length ball, on middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne looks to work it away but gets hit high on his pads.
A length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go this time.
A full ball, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne looks to flick it but gets an inside edge onto his pads. England players are little excited but nothing there in the end.

A length ball, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out solidly towards the on side and shouts NO RUN. So England fail to get a wicket from the new ball and Australia finish with 221-2 at the end of Day 1.
Anderson starts with a good-length delivery, outside off. Steven Smith lets it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, around off. Steven Smith moves across in his crease and blocks it out.
Lovely delivery! This was a good-length ball, around the fourth stump channel and curling away late. Smith looks to poke at it at first but sways away from the line in the end.
FOUR! Steven Smith is up and running on Day 2! Anderson shortens his length, outside off. Smith stays back and cuts it past the point fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length, way outside off. Steven Smith leaves it alone.
On a length, just outside off and angling in late. Steven Smith lets it be.
Broad starts with a length ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne hangs back in his crease to block this one out.
This is a wayward ball, well outside off. Marnus Labuschagne offers no shot to this one.
Much better from Broad! A length ball, angling in from outside off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it off the front foot.
Good-length delivery, jagging back in late, around leg. Marnus Labuschagne looks to block but it goes off the thick inside edge towards fine leg for a run. Labuschagne moves to 96!
Leg bye! Back of a length, around leg. Steven Smith stays back and looks to flick but he misses. The ball ricochets off his thigh pad towards fine leg for a leg bye.
On a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Fuller in length, outside off. Steven Smith stays back and drives it towards mid off.
Anderson bangs it into the deck, around middle and leg. Steven Smith stays back and pulls it along the ground towards deep square leg for one.
Good-length ball, around off and shaping away late. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but he misses and gets hit on his thigh pad.
BEATEN! Back of a length, outside off and curling away a bit. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but the ball whistles past his outside edge.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Short of a length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne gets behind the line of the ball and blocks it.
Short of a length, way outside off. Steven Smith shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length, jagging back in from outside off. Steven Smith leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Steven Smith lets it through to the keeper.
FOUR! Glorious! Fuller in length, outside off. Steven Smith moves across in his crease and caresses it through the cover region for a boundary.
Another full ball, around off. Steven Smith hangs back and pushes it to mid on.
On a length, angling down leg. Steven Smith misses his flick. Jos Buttler does well behind the sticks to move across to his left to gather the ball.

Oh, dear! That came from nowhere! This was a good-length ball, around off and taking off from a length. Marnus Labuschagne looks to block but he gets hit on the shoulder of his bat and he loses the grip on his bat as well.
Good-length delivery, around off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out to cover.

FOUR! Finally, Marnus Labuschagne gets to his sixth Test hundred! Back of a length, outside off. Labuschagne looks to block but it goes off the thick outside edge past the slip cordon and races away to the fence. What a gritty knock this has been from him! He punches the air in delight and gets a hug from his mate, Steven Smith!
On a length, around off and jagging back in late. Marnus Labuschagne looks to leave but gets hit high on his body.
Good-length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it off the front foot.
Fuller in length, drifting down leg. Marnus Labuschagne clips it past the mid-wicket fielder. The fielder there chases it and the batters take a couple.
Good-length ball, angling down leg. Steven Smith misses his flick.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Steven Smith blocks it to cover-point.
Another ball, jagging back in down leg. Steven Smith misses his flick yet again.
Back of a length, jagging back in sharply from outside off. Steven Smith stays back to block but he misses and gets hit high on his pad. A stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Back of a length, outside off. Steven Smith shoulders arms to this one.
Broad goes fuller this time, around leg. Steven Smith looks to flick but gets in a tangle, loses his balance and gets hit on his pad.

NO BALL! Oh, dear! A chance goes begging and Marnus Labuschagne gets a lottery ticket! Ollie Robinson bowls a beauty straightaway, gets the nick and most importantly Jos Buttler takes the catch this time. But Robinson oversteps and the TV umpire confirms that it is a no ball. This was a good-length ball, around the corridor of uncertainty, Marnus Labuschagne looks to block it but gets the thick outside edge towards the keeper. Buttler moves to his right and takes a good catch. The on-field umpire asks Marnus Labuschagne to wait as he checks the front foot of Ollie Robinson. The replays roll in and it suggests that there was nothing behind the line. It is a no ball and the Adelaide crowd erupts. Looks like Christmas came 7 times early for Marnus Labuschagne. The smile on his face as he walks back into the middle says it all.
Full-length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it to mid off and yells No RUN.
Good-length ball, around off. The ball nips away off the deck. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms and lets it go through him.
Fuller and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne tucks it to mid-wicket.
Length, around middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne nudges it to mid-wicket.
LEG BYE! Fuller, on the pads, Marnus Labuschagne misses his flick. The ball goes to square leg off the pads. A leg bye is collected.
Outside off, left alone by Smith. Cricket is a cruel game. Ollie Robinson with a superb over but still he won't be happy about it.
Good-length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne stays back to defend it.
Good-length ball, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out.
Length ball, angling in from middle. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to square leg.

DROPPED! A tough one though! Banged into the deck, around off. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and pulls. Ollie Robinson at square leg hops to his right and stretches out to grab it but he puts it down and the ball goes past him for a run.
Short of a length, way outside off. Steven Smith lets it be.
Back of a length, outside off. Steven Smith leaves it alone.
On a length, angling in from outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne prods but does not offer any shot to this one.
Back of a length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne hangs back and defends it to cover.
Short of a length, way outside off and curling away late. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms to it.

OUT! LBW! Ollie Robinson gets his man this time and he is pumped! Joy for England! This was a length ball, jagging back in sharply after pitching from outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it but the ball nips back late and hits him near the knee roll. Robinson appeals and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. Marnus Labuschagne consults with his partner, Steven Smith and opts for a review. The Hawk Eye indicates three reds and Labuschagne is a goner! Robinson would surely breathe a sigh of relief!
Howout: lbw b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Good-length ball, around off. Travis Head blocks it off the back foot. A wicket-maiden from Robinson!
Good-length ball, around middle. Steven Smith tucks it to the leg side.
Banged into the deck, around leg. Steven Smith ducks under it.

FOUR! Another short ball, around leg. Steven Smith stays back, swivels and pulls it behind square on the leg side. Chris Woakes at deep backward square leg does not pick the ball and the ball races away to the fence.
On a length, around off. Steven Smith blocks it out.
Length ball, around middle. Steven Smith covers the line of the ball and defends it.

Leg bye! Good-length delivery, angling in late from middle. Steven Smith mises his flick and the ball ricochets off his thigh pad towards Haseeb Hameed at leg slip who half-stops it and the batters cross for a leg bye.
On a length, just outside off. Steven Smith moves across in his crease and leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off and jagging back in late. Steven Smith shoulders his arms to it.
Length ball, around off. Steven Smith looks to defend but gets squared up and it goes off the outer half of the blade towards point.
Good-length ball, on off. Steven Smith blocks it off the front foot.
Fuller in length, outside off. Steven Smith presses forward and drives but straight to the mid off fielder.

NO BALL! Good-length delivery, around off and curling away late. Steven Smith gets back in his crease to block but he gets squared up yet again and the ball hits him high on his bat. The umpire signals a no ball as Robinson oversteps.
Length ball, around off. Steven Smith gets behind the line of the delivery and pushes it to mid on.
Woakes serves a length ball, on the pads. Head stays inside the crease and nudges it to square leg.
On a length, around off, angled across the left-hander. Travis Head stays back and blocks it out.
FOUR! Width on offer and Travis Head opens his account with a boundary. Slightly short, outside off. Head stays on the back foot and cuts it through covers for a boundary.
Length and on off. Head blocks it out watchfully. Not getting carried away with that boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Head hops and blocks it onto the deck.
Length ball, on off. Head defends it out watchfully.

SHORT! Good-length ball, around off, nipping away. Steven Smith looks to defend it out, but manages to get an outside edge. The ball goes towards the right of second slip. Rory Burns there dives to his right but the ball lands in front of him.

Enquiry from behind the wickets but the umpire is unmoved! On a length, in the channel of uncertainty. Steven Smith comes across and shoulders his arms. The ball flies of the deck, to clip the thigh pads and go towards the keeper.
A good-length ball, outside off, Smith pushes it to cover.
A full-length ball, on off. Steven Smith defends it out solidly.
BEATEN! Ollie Robinson is on the money yet again. A length ball, on the fourth stump line. Smith covers his off stump and looks to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball, on off. Smith defends it back to the bowler.
Woakes comes 'round the wicket. A length ball, just outside off. Head stays back and taps it to point.
Nice timing! Good-length ball, around off. Head hangs back and punches it through the gap at covers and gets a brace.
Length ball, outside off. Head stays back and cuts it towards point. Not in the gap this time.
Another dot! Good-length ball, angled into the batter. Head defends it out towards mid on.
A length ball, outside off. Head shoulders his arms at it.
Good length and on off. Head defends it to point.
Length ball, outside off. Smith leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good-length ball, in the channel of uncertainty. Smith is persistent on leaving the ball outside his eyeline.
Fuller, around off. Smith prods and defends it out solidly.
Lovely bowling from Ollie Robinson. On a length, on the fourth stump line. Steven Smith shuffles across to play at it, but as the ball curls away late. Smith opts to leave it instead.
Length and on off. Smith blocks it out.
Another maiden for Ollie Robinson. Full-length ball, angled into the batter. Smith defends it to the leg side.
Full length, on off. Head comes inside and plays it to the left of the bowler. Woakes puts his left hand out and stops the ball.
Good-length ball, angled in on off. Head stays back and punches it towards point. Hameed gathers it safely.

EDGED! But does not carry again. Woakes comes over the wicket this time. A length ball, angled across the batter. Head looks to push it away but gets an outside edge towards second slip. Rory Burns dives forward but the ball lands in front of him, as Head plays it with soft hands.
Nice fielding by Malan. A length ball, around off. Head punches it towards cover. Dawid Malan dives to his left and makes a sharp half-stop. The batters cross for a single.
Full and on leg. Smith clips it to deep square leg for a single.
NO BALL! Woakes has overstepped and he has to reload the last delivery again. A length ball, outside off. Head drives it to cover.
FOUR! Crunched! Short and wide, outside off. Head swats it through cover-point and bags a boundary.
Full and outside off. Smith leans forward and blocks it out.
Length and on off. Smith keeps it out watchfully.
Good length, wide outside off. Smith leaves it alone.
Full length and on off. Smith looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards backward point and collects a brace.
Good running this time! A full-length ball, on the pads, Smith clips it through mid-wicket. The batters run three before the fielder cuts it out.
Three leg byes! Touch short and on the pads, Head stays back and misses his flick. It goes towards fine leg off the pads. The batters run three and the umpire signals a leg bye.
Floated, full and outside off. Head pushes it out.
Tossed up, around middle. Head goes back and blocks it back to the bowler.
Looped up, full and on off. Head prods and blocks itout.

Nice turn and bounce this time! Floated, outside off. The ball turns away with some extra bounce. Head looks to cut it away but the bounce beats him. Jos Buttler collects the ball near his chest and clips the bails off. Head had his back leg planted inside the crease.

Full and on off. Head drives it towards mid on. He is out of his crease looking for a single. But Smith is blocked by Root who is ball watching and sends Head back. No trouble for Head, as he gets back safely.
On off, pushed away. A good over by Root.
FOUR! Up and Over! Ben Stokes sticks with his plan of bowling short, but gets punished this time. Back of a length, outside off. Smith hangs back and lofts it over point for a boundary.
WIDE! A sharp bumber, going above Smith's head. Umpire calls it as a wide.
Full-length ball, on off. Smith blocks it out watchfully.
Length and on off. Smith continues to remain solid in his defense.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Smith stays on the back foot and pulls it through mid-wicket for a single.
Short ball and on off. Head defends it out to the off side.
Short ball, going down leg. Head shoulders his arms and leaves it alone for the keeper. A decent start by Stokes.
Flighted, full and on off. Smith advances down the track and pushes it to mid off for a single.
Tossed up, full and on off. Head drives it towards cover.
Darted on the pads, Head clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Nicely guided and another boundary for the Australian skipper. Short and wide outside off. Smith hangs on the back foot and guides it through backward point for a boundary.
Flatter and on off. Smith gets behind the line and blocks it out.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Smith comes forward and defends it out with his pads. Runs are coming in at a really good pace for the hosts.
Back of a length, around the hips. Head clips it to square leg and crosses for a single.

FOUR! EDGED AND OVER! Smith gets his FIFTY in no time. Short ball, around off. The ball is above his head. Smith throws his bat at it and gets an outside edge, as the ball flies over the keeper and into the fine leg fence.
Short and on off. Smith pulls it through square leg for a single.
Back of a length, around off. Head blocks it out and the ball lobs in front of him.
Short ball, into the ribs. Head drags his pull shot towards fine leg for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Smith looks to play the upper cut but gets beaten by the bounce. Another good over for the hosts.
Tossed up, on off. Travis Head blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Top shot! Loopy ball, on a length, around off. Head smacks it over the bowler's head and bags a boundary.

OUT! BOWLED! Joe Root strikes and gets the big wicket of Travis Head! Did him for flight and drift, maybe! Loopy ball, drifting in around leg and then spinning away late. Head looks to flick it across the line but he misses, gets into a tangle and the ball crashes onto his off pole. So the ploy to attack Root hasn't quite worked for Australia! The centurion of the previous game walks back to the hut.
Howout: b Joe Root

Commentary: Overpitched ball, on off. Cameron Green digs it out.
Tossed up, on a length, around leg. Cameron Green turns it to mid on.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Cameron Green stays back and leaves it alone.
Banged into the deck, around leg. Steven Smith swivels and pulls it behind square on the leg side for a run.
First runs in the series for Cameron Green! Length ball, angling in from leg. Green glances it towards fine leg and comes back for the second run.

OUT! BOWLED! That is a peach of a delivery from Stokes and Cameron Green is castled yet again! Stokes hurls a length ball, angling in from off. The ball straightens and goes past Green's defense to knock his off stump over. Green completely misread the line of the delivery as he played for the inswinger! Top stuff from Ben Stokes. Two wickets in two overs for England and they are back in the contest!
Howout: b Ben Stokes

Commentary: Back of a length, on middle. Alex Carey turns it to mid-wicket.
On a length, around off. Alex Carey blocks it off the front foot.
Stokes bangs it into the deck, around off. Alex Carey sways away from the line of the delivery.
Flatter ball, down leg. Steven Smith offers no shot, it hits his pad and the ball goes past the leg slip fielder. The batters don't run though.
Flatter ball, down leg. Steven Smith stays back and nudges it behind square on the leg side for a couple of runs.
A quicker ball, fired down leg. Steven Smith lets it be.
Loopy ball, around leg. Steven Smith tucks it to mid-wicket.
Fuller in length, around off. Steven Smith defends it off the front foot.
Flatter ball, turning down leg. Steven Smith lets it through to the keeper.
Good-length delivery, angling away from the batter. Alex Carey leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, around middle. Alex Carey looks to defend but he misses and gets hit high on his pad.
