FOUR! Banged into the deck, around leg. Carey stays back and swivel-pulls it behind square on the leg side. Dawid Malan runs across to his right from fine leg but he fails to stop the boundary. 300 comes up for Australia!
Short of a length, outside off. Alex Carey punches it to cover.
Leg bye! Length ball, around leg. Alex Carey misses his flick and gets hit on his thigh pad. The ball rolls behind square on the leg side for a leg bye.
A yorker, outside off. Steven Smith sits back and squeezes it out towards backward point.
Tossed up, outside off. Alex Carey gets down on his knee to paddle it down leg but it goes off the toe end towards mid-wicket.
Flatter ball, on off. Alex Carey blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Alex Carey punches it to extra cover.
Loopy ball, around middle. Alex Carey blocks it back to the bowler.
Floated, around off. Alex Carey taps it to backward point and takes off for a quick run.
Fuller in length, around middle. Steven Smith blocks it out.
Length ball, around leg. Alex Carey misses his nudge on the leg side and gets hit on his pad.
Banged into the deck, around middle. Alex Carey ducks underneath.
BEATEN! Good-length delivery, just outside off. Alex Carey looks to poke at it but gets beaten on his outside edge. What a spell this has been from Stokes!
Back of a length, down leg. Alex Carey looks to pull but he gets it from the inner half of his blade towards the leg slip fielder.
Stokes follows it up with a pin-point yorker, around off. Alex Carey digs it out watchfully.
A bumper, around middle. Alex Carey ducks underneath and that will be Dinner on Day 2!
Floated, full and on leg. Smith clips it to deep square leg and gets a single.
Tossed up, full and on off. Alex Carey gets low and reverse-sweeps it towards third man for three runs.
Angled into the pads, Smith goes back and flicks it to fine leg for a single this time.
Looped up, outside off, turning away. Carey defends it to the left of first slip.
Drop and run! Tossed up, outside off, Carey leans forward and defends it to cover. Carey scampers through to the other side for a quick single.
Flatter, around off, spinning in. Smith goes back and pushes it to cover. Australia with a bright start to the second session.
A length ball, on off. Carey stays back and pushes it towards cover. Not in the gap though.
Slightly short, outside off. Carey punches it aggressively towards point, straight to the man there.
Length ball, angled across the left-hander on off. Carey defends it out watchfully.
Good length, on the pads, Carey stays inside the crease and nudges it to mid-wicket.
Five dots in a row! Fuller and on leg. Carey tucks it to mid-wicket. Can Anderson gets his tenth maiden of the game?
Yes, he surely can! This one is quicker, on a good-length, around off, close to the body this time. Carey shoulders his arms at it.
Full and on middle. Smith flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flatter and short, around middle and leg. Smith goes back and punches it through point for a single.
Full and around off. Carey drives it to cover. Stokes gets low and stops it from running past him.
Floated, outside off. Carey pushes it to point for a single.
Full and outside off. Smith prods to the pitch of the ball and defends it out.
Short and wide outside off. Smith shuffles across and shoulders his arms. This one turned in with some bounce.
Back of a length, around off. Carey punches it to cover.
A length ball, around middle and off, Carey pushes it away.
Good-length ball, around off. Carey stays on the back foot and pushes it to covers.
A couple of runs now! A length ball, angled into the batter. Carey stays inside the crease, closes the face of the bat and flicks it through square leg for a brace.
Length and on off. Carey blocks it back to the bowler.
A good over by Anderson, but ain't bothering the batter much! A length ball, on off. Carey defends it to the off side.
Floated, full and outside off. Smith leans forwards and works it to covers for a single.
Root comes 'round the wicket for the left-hander. Flatter, around off, Carey blocks it into the deck.

In the air but safe! Floated, full and on off. Carey chips it over mid off and takes a single. All England players had their eyes on the ball in hope, but it landed just besides the mid off man, who was running back.
Full and on off. Smith pushes it to the off side for a single.
On leg, Carey flicks it to square leg for a single.
Flatter and on middle. Smith blocks it out solidly.
Full length and outside off. Carey leans into his shot and drives it past extra cover for a brace.
Length and outside off. Carey defends it to cover.
Fuller and on off. Carey works it to the left of the bowler.
Good length, angled into the batter on off. Carey hangs back and blocks it out.
On a length, outside off. Carey shoulders his arms at it.
A dot to end another good over by Anderson. Good-length ball, outside off. Some extra bounce this time. Carey shuffles across and leaves it alone for the keeper.
Flatter and outside off. Smith pushes it to point.
On the pads, Smith flicks it to square leg for a single.
Short and outside off. Carey helps it towards point.
FOUR! Up and over! Flighted, full and on off. Carey gets under it and lifts it over mid off. A few bounces and the ball goes into the boundary.
Flatter and short, outside off, Carey cuts it through point for a single.
FOUR! Slapped and clouted to the ropes! Tossed up, full and outside off. Smith leans into it and drives it through covers to bag the second boundary of the over.
Anderson comes in from 'round the wicket. Length ball, angled into the batter. Carey flicks it to the leg side.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Carey tucks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping in. Carey punches it to cover.
A length ball, outside off. Carey stays back and defends it to point.
Length and on the pads. Carey defends it to short mid-wicket.
Around the hips, Carey tucks it to square leg for a single.
A full-length ball, around middle and off. Carey defends it back to the bowler off the front foot.
BEATEN! A length ball, around off, shaping away from the left-hander. Carey looks to defend it out but gets beaten at the outside edge.
Length and on off. Carey blocks it to short mid off.
Four dots on the trot now! Length and outside off, angled across the batter. Carey gets behind the line and defends it onto the pitch.
Good-length ball, outside off. Carey watches it sail past him.
Full length and outside off, Carey works it to mid on off the inner half. This is the eleventh maiden over for Robinson.
Woakes starts with a good-length ball, outside off. Steven Smith leaves it alone.
Goes fuller this time, outside off. Steven Smith prods and lets it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, well outside off. Steven Smith does not offer any shot to it.
Length ball, around off. Steven Smith presses forward and looks to block but it goes off the thick outside edge towards Rory Burns at second slip, on the bounce.
This is a wayward ball, down leg. Smith leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Length ball, angling in from off. Steven Smith presents the full face of his bat and blocks it back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery, around off. Alex Carey prods to defend but it goes off the outer half of the bat towards backward point.
Back of a length, around off. Alex Carey rides the bounce nicely and blocks it to cover.
Short of a length, outside off. Alex Carey stays back and looks to push it through covers but he gets it from the inner half of his blade towards mid on.
Back of a length, around leg. Alex Carey tucks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, outside off. Alex Carey looks for a booming drive but finds Jonny Bairstow (sub) at covers who half-stops it.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Alex Carey presses forward and defends it back to the bowler. Another maiden over from Robinson!
Back of a length, around off. Steven Smith blocks it off the back foot.
On a length, around middle. Steven Smith gets behind the line of the ball and defends it.
Fuller in length, outside off. Steven Smith prods and blocks it to cover.
Short of a length, outside off. Steven Smith looks to block but it goes off the outer half of the bat towards backward point.

NO BALL and FOUR! Edged but it sneaks through the first and the second slip fielder! This was a good-length ball, outside off. Smith hangs back and has a tentative poke at it. It takes the outside edge and goes in between the slip cordon for a boundary. Woakes oversteps and the umpire signals a No Ball. Imagine, if this catch would've been taken. This would've played with the heads of the English players yet again.
Back of a length, outside off. Steven Smith leaves it alone.
FOUR! CARESSED! Length ball, outside off. Smith presses forward, reaches out and carves it past the mid off fielder for another boundary.
Good-length delivery, angling across the batter. Alex Carey leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, around leg. Carey looks to block but it goes off the thick inside edge towards fine leg for a run.
Short of a length, around middle. Steven Smith moves across in his crease and looks to flick but he misses and gets hit high on his body.
Length delivery, angling down leg. Steven Smith misses his flick and the ball ricochets off his thigh pad to the leg slip fielder.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. Steven Smith turns it to mid-wicket.
Robinson hurls a full ball, angling in from off. Steven Smith prods and defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller in length, around middle. Alex Carey pushes it to mid on.

FOUR! Not where Carey intended it to go but he will take that! Back of a length, outside off. Carey stays back and slashes hard. It goes off the thick outside edge past the gully fielder and into the fence.
Good-length ball, around leg. Alex Carey glances it to fine leg and collects a single.
SIX! What a shot! First maximum of the innings! On a length, around off. Smith gets low, swivels underneath it and smokes it over the deep mid-wicket region for a biggie. 350 comes up for Australia!
Good-length delivery, around off. Steven Smith blocks it out.
Fuller in length, around off. Steven Smith pushes it to mid off.
Back of a length, way outside off. Alex Carey leaves it alone.
Short of a length, angling in from off. Alex Carey punches it to cover.
Fuller in length, outside off. Alex Carey drives but straight to the mid off fielder.
On a length, just outside off. Alex Carey prods and square drives it past the point fielder for a couple of runs.

Edged but falls short of the slip fielder yet again! Frustration continues for England! This was a good-length delivery, outside off. Carey looks to drive on the up but he gets a thick outside edge which lands just in front of Joe Root at first slip.
Good-length ball, outside off. Carey drives it past the diving cover fielder and bags a couple of runs.
Length ball, around middle. Steven Smith blocks it out.
Fuller in length, darted on the pads. Smith clips it past the diving mid-wicket fielder for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Alex Carey stays back and steers it towards the gully fielder who half-stops it and the batters take a run.
Good-length ball, on middle. Steven Smith defends it solidly.
Short of a length, around off pole. Steven Smith stays back and keeps it out.
On a length, just outside off. Steven Smith looks to block but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards backward point.
Good-length ball, angling in from middle. Alex Carey turns it to mid-wicket.
On a length, around off. Alex Carey defends it off the front foot.
Stokes goes fuller this time, around off. Alex Carey pushes it back to the bowler.
Banged into the deck, around leg. Alex Carey looks to pull but he fails to get any bat on it.

Sloppy from Zak Crawley (sub) at covers. Good-length ball, outside off. Alex Carey punches it through the cover region. Crawley puts in a dive at covers but throws it to the striker's end which was completely needless. The batters take a couple.
FOUR! SMASHED! Length ball, outside off. Alex Carey caresses it past the extra cover fielder for a boundary.

BEATEN! Back of a length, around off and shaping away a bit. Smith hangs back and looks to block but the ball zips past his outside edge. That really moved a lot. Even Smith, who rarely opens his mouth while batting, could not stop saying, 'Oh, my word!'
On a length, around middle. Steven Smith blocks it off the front foot.
Good-length delivery, around off. Steven Smith blocks it towards cover-point.
Back of a length, around off. Steven Smith gets behind the line of the ball to defend it.
This was angled in around middle. Smith turns it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, around leg. Steven Smith glances it and the ball goes just past the leg slip fielder for a run.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Steven Smith tucks it to mid-wicket.
Short of a length, around off. Steven Smith stays back and blocks it off the back foot.
Good-length delivery, around leg. Steven Smith nudges it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Back of a length, around leg. Alex Carey tucks it to the leg side.
Fuller in length, outside off. Alex Carey drives but straight to the cover fielder.
Short of a length, outside off. Carey rides the bounce nicely and taps it to backward point.

Overthrows and it is five! A full-length ball, on off. Smith defends it to cover and missed his attempt at the non-striker's end. The ball runs past the fielder who dives to cover it and goes into the fence at long on.
FOUR! Pulled away! A short ball, on off. Carey stays back and pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Fuller and outside off. Carey leans in and drives it to extra cover.
Length and around off. Carey punches it to point. Pope dives to his right to make a good stop.
Good length, on off. Carey presses forward and defends it out.
A single to end a good over for Australia. Full and on off. Carey drives it through covers to get to the other end.
Play and a miss! Stokes comes from 'round the wicket. A length ball, around leg. Carey makes room and looks to crunch it through covers but misses.
Short and on the body, Carey swivel and pulls it behind square on the on side for a single.
Fuller and on off. Smith caresses it towards cover for a single. He moves to 88.
Touch short, on the pads, Carey misses his flick. The ball balloons off the thigh pads, to the right of Buttler.
Short and on middle. Carey pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Classy batting from Smith. Back of a length, around off. Smith wait for the ball and pokes it over the slip cordon to bag a boundary at third man. He moves to 92 now.
Full-length ball, angled across the batter on off. Carey presses forward and defends it out.
Length ball  around off. Carey looks to defend it out, but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
A length ball, around middle and off. Carey gets an inside edge, the ball rolls out to the slip cordon.
Length and on off. Carey defends it out solidly.
Good length, on off. Carey defends it out watchfully. He is just 2 runs away from his maiden Test half-century. Does not want to play any risky shots now.
A length ball, around middle and off. Carey shuffles across and looks to flick it away. The ball rolls out to the off side off the outer half.
Fuller and on off, at 125 kph. Smith stays back and just blocks it out.
Length and on the pads. Smith comes inside the line and flicks it towards fine leg for a single. He moves to 93.
A single for Carey now! Length and on the pads, Carey stays back and flicks it to deep square leg for a single. He moves to 49.
On a length, around off. Smith shuffles across, closes the face of the bat and tucks it to short mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, on the fourth stump line. Smith comes across and blocks it to the leg side off the inner half.

OUT! LBW! James Anderson gets his first wicket of the game and sends back the Australian skipper, Steven Smith, back to the pavilion. Nervous 90s they say and the experienced seamer Anderson hands a crucial breakthrough for his side. He was agonisingly close to his century, and shakes his head as he walks out of the field. A full-length ball, outside off. The ball nips in a long way. Smith shuffles across and looks to defend it out, but misses and gets struck on the pads. James Anderson appeals and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. Smith goes for the review. The RTS shows no bat is involved. The Ball Tracker shows it is umpire's call on impact and the ball is hitting the wickets. Smith has to walk back.
Howout: lbw b James Anderson

Commentary: MAIDEN TEST FIFTY for Alex Carey! Back of a length, on the hips, Carey flicks it to square leg and scampers through for a single.
Good-length ball, angled across the left-hander. Starc leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off. Starc helps it towards mid on.
Full and on the stumps, Starc defends it out watchfully.
Short and around the hips, Starc stays back and flicks it to the leg side.
Fuller and on leg. Starc clips it to deep mid-wicket and collects the brace.
Length ball, outside off. Carey defends it out watchfully.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Carey flicks it to the leg side for a single.
Length and on the pads, Starc flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one bites the dust. James Anderson picks up his second wicket in the space of two overs. A length ball, around off. Alex Carey plays it on the up and lifts it towards cover. Haseeb Hameed keeps his eyes on the ball, dives to his right and pouches it safely. He was a bit sloppy in the field, since the first Test match, but this catch was a crucial one and he does not drop this one. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2!
Howout: c Haseeb Hameed b James Anderson

Commentary: Good-length ball, on middle. Michael Neser blocks it towards mid on.
Fuller in length this time, around leg. Michael Neser flicks but straight to the square leg fielder.
Length ball, around middle. Mitchell Starc blocks it out.
This is a good-length delivery, well outside off. Mitchell Starc leaves it alone.
Short of a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc punches it to cover.

FOUR! Uppish but well over the mid-wicket fielder! Full ball, darted on the pads. Starc flicks it uppishly and the ball flies over James Anderson at mid-wicket who hops to take the catch. It races away to the fence.
Back of a length, down leg. Starc glances it to fine leg and takes a run.

FOUR! First runs in Test cricket for Michael Neser! Good-length ball, just outside off and shaping away late. Neser looks to defend but it goes off the thick outside edge past the slip cordon for a boundary.
Full ball, on middle. Mitchell Starc works it past the short mid on fielder and collects a run. 400 comes up for Australia now!
On a length, around off. Michael Neser blocks it off the front foot.
Short of a length, outside off. Michael Neser stays back, rides the bounce well and cuts it to backward point.
Good-length delivery, nipping back in late. Michael Neser looks to block but that ball came back in a long away and went past Neser's defense to hit him high on his pad.
Length ball, outside off. Michael Neser looks to defend but it goes off the thick outside edge past the gully fielder for a couple.
Back of a length, outside off. Michael Neser rocks back and cuts it wide of backward point for a run.
Short of a length, around off. Michael Neser stays back and blocks it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, around leg. Michael Neser nudges it behind square on the leg side for a run.
Length ball, angling in from outside off. Mitchell Starc leaves it alone.
In the air...but safe! Good-length ball, around off. Starc looks to heave it away across the line but it goes off the thick outside edge over the slip cordon for a couple of runs.
Back of a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc heaves it towards deep mid-wicket and collects a single.

FOUR! Nicely done! Banged in short, outside off. Michael Neser hangs back and pulls it in front of square to collect a boundary. Ollie Pope at deep mid-wicket dives to his left to stop the ball but he fails to do so.
Length ball, angling in from off. Mitchell Starc blocks it off the front foot.
This is a good-length ball, around off. Mitchell Starc blocks it to covers.
Back of a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc punches it to cover.
Fuller in length, outside off. Starc looks to go downtown but he miscues it and the ball goes just over Stuart Broad at mid on. The batters take a couple of runs.
On a length, around middle and leg. Mitchell Starc works it to mid on and takes off for a single.
Back of a length, around off. Michael Neser tucks it to mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, on off. Mitchell Starc stays back and pushes it back to the bowler.
Full-length delivery, outside off. Mitchell Starc digs it out towards mid off and rotates the strike.
Length ball, around leg. Michael Neser flicks it to deep square leg and takes one.
Back of a length, around middle. Mitchell Starc tucks it to the leg side.
Back of a length, around off. Mitchell Starc looks to heave it to the leg side but he misses and gets hit on his thigh pad.
Fuller in length, outside off. Mitchell Starc works it to mid off and keeps the strike for the next over by taking a run.
Back of a length, around middle. Mitchell Starc pulls it along the ground towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.
FOUR! Edged and boundary! Back of a length, outside off. Michael Neser looks to pull but it goes off the top edge and flies over the keeper for a boundary.

NOT OUT! England lose all of their reviews now! This was a short-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Neser backs away and looks to cut but he misses. Chris Woakes appeals but the umpire is unmoved. Joe Root opts for a review but the RTS confirms that there is no bat involved and the on-field decision remains.
FOUR! SHOT! Full ball, around off. Michael Neser stays back and strokes it past the mid on fielder for a boundary.
SIX! Even better shot! Neser is having some fun out there! Shorter in length, outside off. Neser sits back and cuts it over the deep point fence for a biggie.
Full ball, outside off. Neser drives it the cover fielder who fumbles and the batters take a run.
A slower ball, on a length, around leg. Michael Neser stays back and helps it on its way towards fine leg for a single.
Good change of pace from Stokes! Another slower ball, fuller in length, outside off. Mitchell Starc looks to slog but gets deceived by it and leaves it in the end.
DROPPED! A full toss, around off. Mitchell Starc his it straight back to Stokes who fails to collect it cleanly. The ball goes past him for a run.

FOUR! WHACKED! Another slower ball, on a length, around middle. Michael Neser gets low and heaves it behind square on the leg side for a boundary. There were fielders set in the deep, but Neser manages to find the gap.
Banged into the deck, outside off. Michael Neser lets it be.
Banged into the deck, yet again, around off. Neser pulls it to deep mid-wicket for one. That brings up the 50-run partnership between these two!
Back of a length, outside off. Michael Neser looks to heave it across the line but it goes off the inner half of the blade behind square on the leg side for a run.
FOUR! Cut away! Short of a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc stays back and cuts it past the point fielder for a boundary.
Wide! Woakes hurls a slower ball but way outside off. Mitchell Starc leaves it alone. Wide called by the umpire.
Play and a miss! Good-length ball, angling across the batter. Mitchell Starc looks to tonk it over long on but fails to get any blade on it.
A slower ball, fuller in length, way outside off. Mitchell Starc looks to slog but the ball goes past his bat.

DROPPED! A tough one though! Length ball, outside off. Mitchell Starc heaves it uppishly towards the mid-wicket region. Ollie Pope runs in from the deep, reaches there but drops it in the end. The batters take a couple.
Back of a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc shuffles across and looks to scoop it over the keeper but he misses.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is a seriously good catch from Stuart Broad. Length ball, just outside off. Neser looks to go downtown but he gets the toe end of his bat and the ball balloons in the air behind the mid on fielder. Stuart Broad at mid on backtracks, keeps his eyes on the ball and takes a good catch. End of an entertaining innings from the debutant. Broad is making his teammate know that he could not see the ball. The lights were right in the eyes and that's why he tumbled into the ground as he grabbed the ball.
Howout: c Stuart Broad b Ben Stokes

Commentary: FOUR! Top shot! Back of a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc stays back and cuts it past the point fielder for a boundary.
FOUR! BACK-TO-BACK BOUNDARIES! Length ball, in the slot, around off. Starc stays back and smokes it over the bowler's head for another boundary.
A slower ball, on a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc looks to heave it to the leg side but he gets an under-edge towards the keeper.
Wide! Stokes bangs it into the deck, around middle. Mitchell Starc misses his pull and the umpire calls it a wide for height!
FOUR! UP AND OVER! Banged into the pitch, around middle. Starc looks to pull but it goes off the top edge and flies over the keeper for a boundary.
Fuller in length, around middle. Mitchell Starc works it to long on for a couple of runs.

Jhye Richardson is up and running straightaway!! This is a length ball, on off. Richardson looks to slog it over long on but he does not middle it and the ball goes just over Ben Stokes at mid on. The batters take three runs.
Fuller and outside off. Starc carves it over cover and gets a single.

SIX! Jhye Richardson frees his arms this time. A short ball, around middle and leg. Jhye Richardson stands tall and smokes it over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie. The team-mates in the pavilion are loving it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Short ball, on off. Jhye Richardson looks to heave it away. The ball takes the outside edge and Jos Buttler takes the catch safely, unlike on Day 1. Steven Smith signals from the pavilion. AUSTRALIA DECLARE AT 473/9.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Chris Woakes

Commentary: Full-length ball, wide outside off. Haseeb Hameed leaves it alone. He would be glad that it was not on the stumps and did not trouble him.
Length ball, way outside off, shaping away. Haseeb Hameed leaves it alone for the keeper.
That's better! Seems back off the deck. Good-length ball, on the fourth stump line. The ball nips in off the deck. Haseeb Hameed shoulders his arms and the ball goes off the off pole.
Good shot! A full-length ball, outside off. Hameed leans in and crunches it through covers. The fielder gives it a chase and pulls it back in time near the ropes. The batters take three runs.

Burns plays it very cautiously knowing what happened with him last time around! A full-length ball, around middle and leg. This one straightens a bit off the deck, Burns stays back and defends it to the leg side.

FOUR! Rory Burns gets off the mark with a boundary. Fuller and on the pads, Rory Burns stays back and flicks it through mid-wicket. The ball races away into the fence. A positive start for the visitors, 7 runs coming off the first over.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Hameed leaves it for the keeper.
A length ball, outside off. The ball seams away yet again. Hameed keeps the blade close to his body and lets it sail past him.

BEATEN! Jhye Richardson causing early problems. On a length, outside off, nips in a touch. Haseeb Hameed looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge. The keeper, Alex Carey catches it on his left.
Length and outside off, Hameed leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full-length ball, on middle and leg. Haseeb Hameed squeezes it towards square leg. Not in the gap though.
BEATEN AGAIN! What a beauty! Jhye Richardson starts his spell with a maiden. A length ball, around off, nipping away. The ball beats the outside edge.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mitchell Starc sends back Rory Burns yet again in this Test series. Australia get the dream start they were looking for. Starc serves it quicker, back of a length, around off. Rory Burns shuffles across and looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the second slip. Steven Smith is placed there who makes no mistake and pouches it comfortably.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Malan gets off the mark. Good-length ball, outside off. Malan defends it towards cover and gets across for a single.
Nicely placed! Fuller and outside off. Hameed leans in and drives it through covers. Head recovers the ball near the ropes. The batters take three runs.
LEG BYE! Back of a length, around the hips. Malan misses his flick. The ball takes the thigh pads and runs towards fine leg. The batters collect a leg bye.
Outside off, left alone by Hameed.
A length ball, outside off, moving away. Hameed lets it go to the keeper. End of a successful over By Mitchell Starc.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away from the left-hander. Malan leaves it alone for the keeper.
On a length, moving away from the left-hander. Malan holds his defensive pose and lets the ball goes past him.
Another swinging away, on a fuller length. Malan does not chase this either.
On a length, outside off, shaping away. Malan shoulders his arms.
Full-length ball, outside off. Malan presses forward and defends it out watchfully.
Another maiden over for Jhye Richardson. A length ball, around middle and off, shaping away. This is close to the body but Malan lets it go past him.
Good-length ball, outside off, moving away. Hameed shoulders his arms and leaves it alone.
Touch fuller, outside off, some extra bounce off the deck. Haseeb Hameed does not chase this one.
Starc makes Hameed play this time. Good-length ball, on off. Hameed stays inside the crease and blocks it out solidly.
Back of a length, on off. Hameed shoulders his arms. He trusts the bounce this time and sees the cherry go above the off pole.
Good length, outside off, nipping away. Hameed lets it go to the keeper.
Full length and outside off, Hameed looks to crunch it through the off side but miscues it. The ball takes the inner half and lands on the deck. First maiden for Mitchell Starc in this Test game.
On a length, around off. Malan hangs back and taps it towards point.
Good-length ball, outside off, the ball straightens a bit after hitting the deck. Malan stays back and shoulders his arms.
A length ball sliding down leg. Malan leaves it alone. Carey moves to his right to collect the ball.
A length ball, around off. Malan defends it out watchfully.
Good length and outside off. Malan leaves it alone for the keeper.
A length ball, around off. Malan defends it out solidly. Third consecutive maiden for Jhye Richardson.
Full-length ball, on off. Hameed stays back and blocks it out towards gully off the outer half, as he gets squared up here.

OUT! CAUGHT! Michael Neser gets his maiden Test wicket in his first over. His teammates love it. A full-length ball, around middle and leg. Haseeb Hameed stays inside the crease and flicks it aerially towards short mid-wicket. Mitchell Starc is placed at the right place and takes the simplest of catches to put the visitors in a spot of trouble already. You can call this a poor shot, or what was the need to play the ball in the air and so on. But this is where Smith's captaincy has to be given a nod. That man was strategically placed there, because Hameed has this habit of slicing the ball in the air, while getting across the line and looking to play on the leg side.
Howout: c Mitchell Starc b Michael Neser

Commentary: Outside off, left alone by Root.

EDGED AND SHORT! Good-length ball, on the fourth stump line. Root hangs his bat out, as he looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and lands short of Steven Smith at second slip. A sigh of relief in the English camp.
Three runs! On a length, outside off. Root stays back and guides it past the gully fielder. Nathan Lyon gives it a chase and keeps it down to three.
Good-length ball, on off. Malan hangs back and blocks it out watchfully.
Length ball, on the pads, Root flicks it to square leg.
Good-length ball, on off. Root defends it to the off side.
Good length and on off. Root defends it out solidly.
Back of a length, outside off. Root gets back and blocks it to point.
Fuller and outside off. Root leans in a drives it past mid off for a single.
Good length and shaping away, outside off, Malan shoulders his arms.

Length and on off. Root defends it to cover for a single. Good running this time. Root and Malan need to make sure to keep changing the strike here to get that left-hand/ right-hand combination in play.
Good-length ball, outside off, moving away. Malan leaves it alone.
Length and on off. Malan defends it out watchfully.

Back of a length, outside off, moving away. And just as Neser released the ball, there was a huge flash around the ground. Malan leaves it alone though. The umpire have decided to stop the play for now.
What a delivery first up! Length ball, just outside off. Dawid Malan prods to block but the ball jags away and Malan sways away from the line of the delivery in the end.
On a length, around off. Dawid Malan presses forward and blocks it to cover.
NO BALL! Good-length ball, angling in from off. Joe Root defends it solidly. Jhye Richardson oversteps and the umpire signals a no ball.
Back of a length, outside off. Root stays back and punches it past the cover fielder for a run. England are up and running on Day 3!
This is a length ball, around off. Dawid Malan hangs back and blocks it to covers.

FOUR! STREAKY! Richardson hurls a full ball, angling across the left-hander. Malan prods and look for a booming drive but it goes off the thick inside edge past the keeper and into the fine leg fence.
Short of a length, outside off. Dawid Malan leaves it alone watchfully.
Good-length delivery, around the fourth stump channel. Dawid Malan lets it through to the keeper.
A bit fuller this time, outside off and angling across the batter. Malan shoulders his arms to this one.
Sweetly timed. A full-length ball, on off. Root stays back and drives it past mid on. The batters take three runs before the fielder cuts it out.
Good-length ball, moving across the batter. Malan leaves it alone for the keeper.
On a length, outside off. Malan shoulders his arms at it.

EDGY! A full-length ball, on the fourth stump line. Malan looks to drive it through covers but plays at it without any foot movement. The ball takes the inside edge and goes towards square leg. They take a single.
LEG BYE! Back of a length, on the body, Root hops and looks to tuck it away. The ball takes the thigh pad and rolls towards fine leg. They collect a leg bye.
Short ball, outside off, Malan is not interested in playing that one.
Fuller and on off. Root gets behind and blocks it out to point.
Slightly short and on the fourth stump line. Root opens the face of the bat late and tries to steer it past gully. The fielder dives to his right to make a good stop.
FOUR! Opens the face of the bat late but this time through the gap. Good-length ball, around off. Root goes back in the crease and steers it past backward point for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Root pushes it towards cover. Not in the gap though.
Drop and run! Touch fuller and on off. Root defends it to cover and scampers across for a single.

Length and on off. Malan stays back and taps it towards point. Malan gets across for a single and retains the strike. Jhye Richardson is unable to ask question to the batsman, unlike the last session on Day 2. He will try to focus on getting that edge into play, sooner than later.
Outside off, Malan leaves it alone for the keeper.
A touch short and on leg, Malan stays back and flicks it to square leg for a single.
Full and on the pads, Root flicks it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, wide of off. Root plays it late and defends it out.
Short and outside off. Root leaves it alone.
Length and on off. Root gets behind the line and defends it out.
Length, around leg. Malan defends it on the back foot.
Touch short and around leg. Malan blocks it to the leg side.
Full-length ball, coming across the left-hander. Malan presses forward and ends up inside edging it onto the pads.
Back of a length, around off. Malan defends it to point and yells 'NO RUN'.
FOUR! Down the ground with ease! A full-length ball, on off. Malan stays back and drives it past mid off. The ball races away to the fence. He does not hit it hard but caresses it instead.
Full, around middle and leg. Malan flicks it to square leg and gets a single.
FOUR! Mitchell Starc starts with a loosener! A short ball, wide outside off. Malan stays back and upper cuts it over the point region for a boundary.
FOUR! Short again by Starc and the result is the same. Back of a length, outside off. Malan stays on the back foot and slashes it towards backward point for a boundary.
Length and on the pads, Malan defends it out.
Better from Starc! Good-length ball, outside off, nips in late though. Malan shoulders his arms and lets it go to the keeper.
Full and straight, on off. Malan drives it past mid off. The batters take three runs before the fielder cuts it out.
OUCH! Good length and around the hips. Some extra bounce off the deck. Root hangs back, hops and looks to flick it away but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Back of a length, outside off. Dawid Malan prods and leaves it alone.
Short of a length, around leg. Dawid Malan tucks it to mid-wicket.
Nicely done! Good-length ball, outside off. Dawid Malan presses forward and pushes it past the cover fielder for a couple of runs.
Length ball, outside off. Dawid Malan looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge past the diving slip fielder for a single.
Good-length ball, around leg. Joe Root nudges it behind square on the leg side for a brace.
Fuller in length, way outside off. Dawid Malan lets it be.
Starc serves a pin-point yorker, around off. Root is up to the task as he digs it out watchfully.
Back of a length, outside off. Joe Root shoulders arms to this one.
Fuller in length, around middle. Joe Root prods and pushes it to mid on.
On a length, way outside off. Joe Root does not offer any shot to this one.
Good-length delivery, around off. Joe Root blocks it to the cover-point region.
Another yorker, outside off. Root reaches out and digs it out behind square on the off side.
Full-length delivery, outside off. Dawid Malan prods and drives it past the mid off fielder. The fielder there gives it a chase and the batters take three runs.

Good-length ball, outside off. Joe Root hangs back to block but he gets a thick outside edge which falls short of the third slip fielder. The fielder there fails to stop it cleanly and the batters sneak in a couple.
On a length, around off. Joe Root blocks it out.
Length ball, jagging back in from middle. Joe Root prods and pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length, outside off. Joe Root stays back, rides the bounce well and blocks it past the cover fielder for a quick run.

A run out chance goes begging! Good-length ball, on off. Dawid Malan taps it to cover and takes off for a single. Root at the non-striker's end is late to react. Travis Head runs in from mid off, collects the ball but misses his shy at the striker's end. A very wayward throw by Head!
Good-length ball, around off. Dawid Malan leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around off. Dawid Malan blocks it to cover.
Banged into the deck, around off. Dawid Malan gets low and lets it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, on middle. Dawid Malan stays back to defend it.
Back of a length, outside off. Dawid Malan hangs back, opens the face of his bat and steers it past the backward point fielder for a couple of runs.
Good-length ball, angling in from off. Dawid Malan stays back to block but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Joe Root prods and pushes it to the cover region for a single.
Flatter ball, around middle. Dawid Malan stays back and tucks it to square leg.
A bit quicker, fuller in length, outside off. Malan defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up, around off. Dawid Malan blocks it solidly.
A bit shorter, outside off. Malan waits for the turn and then works it to backward point.
Flatter ball, on a length, around off. Dawid Malan blocks it out to cover.
Slightly short, around the hips. Joe Root stays back and defends it to the leg side.
A full-length delivery, outside off. Root shoulders his arms at it.
Good-length, around off. Root defends it towards point.
Length and on off, Root gets behind the line really well and follows it with a solid block. Looks like Root is not happy with his blade, maybe it got damaged. Root waits for the options to come out.
Fuller length, on the pads, Root stays back and defends it back to the bowler.
Touch short, on leg. Root stays back and defends it out. A maiden for Starc.

Floated, full and on off, turning away. Malan presses forward and hits it on the up, only on the thigh of the silly point fielder. The ball bounces back onto the deck, but Marnus Labuschagne could not react quickly.
JAFFA! Good spin and bounce this time. Tossed up, around off. Malan presses forward and looks to defend it out, but gets beaten by the turn. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Full and on off Malan defends it out.
Looped up, on off. Malan pushes it towards extra cover and gets off the mark.
In the air but safe! Full and on leg. Root gets low and slog sweeps it towards deep square leg. The balls lands safely and they take a run.
Tossed up, full and on off. Malan pushes it to cover, but not in the gap.
Length and on off. Root defends solidly.
Length and outside off. Root steps forward and defends it out.
BEATEN! This one shapes away off the deck. Good-length ball, around off. Root shuffles across and looks to defend it out. The balls nips away and Root gets beaten on the outside edge.
A length ball, outside off, nips in a bit. Root stays back and blocks it out.
Very full and around off. Root squeezes it out towards backward point and gets a single.
Length and on off. Malan defends it onto the deck.
FOUR! Nice use of the feet this time! Tossed up, full and on off. Root advances forward and lifts it towards long on. Two bounces and into the ropes.
Short and on the pads, Root uses the depth of the crease and flicks it through square leg for a single.

FOUR! Now, Malan gets into the act. Short and outside off, turning away. Malan stays on the back foot and cuts it through covers for a boundary. He did not direct it well, but would be glad it went past the fielder.
Full and on off, Malan defends it on the front foot.
Looped up, outside off. Malan leaves it alone for the keeper.
Floated, full and outside off. Malan does not chase this one.
Full ball, on middle and leg. Root flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
EDGY! A full-length ball, outside off. Malan looks to drive it away, but inside-edges it towards fine leg for a single.
Length and on around off, nips in a bit. Root presses forward and blocks it out solidly.
Good length and on the fourth stump line.Root shuffles across and blocks it watchfully.
Full and on leg. Root clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played. Good-length ball, outside off. Malan stays on the back foot and punches it behind the point fielder. Lyon gives it a chase but the ball wins the race.
Flatter ball, on off, turning in late. Joe Root blocks it out.
Another ball, shorter in length, outside off and spinning in sharply. Root stays back and punches it to the point fielder.
A bit quicker, on a length, outside off. Joe Root blocks it to the point region.
Nicely tossed up, around middle. Joe Root prods and works it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball, outside off and turning in late. Joe Root gets back in his crease and then pushes it behind square on the off side.

FOUR! Root brings out the reverse sweep now! Loopy ball, on a length, outside off. Joe Root gets low and reverse sweeps it past the backward point fielder. Travis Head gives it a chase but the ball wins.
Banged into the deck, down leg. Dawid Malan ducks underneath!
Neser follows it up with a length ball, outside off and angling across the left-hander. Malan stays back and leaves it alone.
Back of a length, angling in from middle. Malan looks to block but it goes off the thick inside edge towards fine leg for a couple of runs.
Length ball, angling in from off. Malan looks to defend by staying back in the crease but he gets an inside edge onto his pads. Luckily for Malan, the ball does not pop out back to the bowler.

Just short of the slip fielder! Good-length delivery, around off and curling away late. Malan looks to poke at it but he gets a thick outside edge which lands just in front of Steven Smith at third slip.
Full ball, on middle. Dawid Malan drives it back past the bowler and collects a couple of runs.
Lyon tosses it nicely, around off. Root gets low and sweeps it nicely to deep backward square leg for one.
Nice and full again, around off. Malan gets forward to block it well.
Flatter ball, around off. Malan gets the thick inside edge towards square leg for a single.
Root is sweeping nicely now. This goes to deep square leg for one. We can see more batters play this shot against Lyon.
Lyon drags his length back a bit and bowls this outside off. Malan stays in the crease to block it but the ball turns away and goes past the outside edge.
Nicely pushed off the front foot past covers for one.
Back of a length, around off. Dawid Malan hangs back, opens the face of his bat and guides it to the slip fielder, on the bounce.
Short of a length, around leg. Dawid Malan pulls it to fine leg and collects a single. Fifty for Malan and this is his ninth in Test cricket! Not the most convincing though but he'll take that!

NOT OUT! Joe Root survives and Australia lose a review! This is a length ball, angling in from outside off. Root looks to defend off the front foot but he misses and gets rapped in front. Michael Neser appeals and the umpire says no. Steven Smith opts for a review but the Hawk Eye suggests that the ball would have gone well over the sticks so the on-field decision remains.
Back of a length, on off. Joe Root stays back and blocks it out.
Good-length ball, outside off. Joe Root defends it solildy.
Length ball, jagging back in slightly from outside off. Joe Root prods to block this one out.
Tossed up, outside off. Dawid Malan defends it to the point region and takes off for a run.
Loopy ball, on middle. Joe Root turns it past the short leg fielder.
Flatter ball, shorter in length, outside off and turning in late. Joe Root tucks it to the leg side.
Another ball, shorter in length, around middle. Joe Root eases it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball, way outside off. Joe Root stays back and does not offer any shot to this one.
A stifled appeal from behind the sticks but the umpire is not interested! Flatter ball, fuller in length, around leg. Joe Root looks to sweep but he misses and gets hit low on his pad.
Back of a length, outside off. Dawid Malan punches it to cover.

Nicely played! Full ball, on middle and leg. Dawid Malan drives it past Mitchell Starc at mid on who dives to stop the ball but the ball goes past him and the batters collect three runs. 100 comes up for England.
FOUR! Top shot! Back of a length, outside off. Joe Root stays back, rides the bounce nicely and punches it past the cover fielder to bag a boundary.
On a length, around off. Joe Root defends it out.
Length ball, around off. Joe Root presents the full face of the bat and pushes it straight back to hit the stumps at the non-striker's end.
Fuller in length, on middle and leg. Joe Root presses forward and works it to mid on.
Flatter ball, on off. Dawid Malan blocks it out.
Flatter and quicker, on a length, around off. Dawid Malan presses forward and defends it solidly.
FOUR! CARESSED! Tossed up, on a length, outside off and spinning away late. Dawid Malan prods and carves it past the cover fielder to collect a boundary.
Flatter ball, on off. Dawid Malan defends it off the front foot.
On a length, around off. Dawid Malan keeps it out watchfully.
A bt quicker, on a length, around off. Dawid Malan stays back and looks to cut but it goes off the shoulder of his bat to backward point.
Back of a length, just outside off. Joe Root hangs back, rides the bounce well and taps it with soft hands to the gully region.
BEAUTY! Length ball, oustide off and angling in late. Root leaves it alone and the ball goes just past his off pole.
Good-length ball, around off. Joe Root gets solid in his defense.
BEATEN! Good-length delivery, jagging back in sharply. Root prods to defend but the ball straightens a bit after pitching and goes past his outside edge.
Fuller in length, outside off. Joe Root drives it past the cover fielder but manages only a single as he did not time it that well. The stand moves to 98.
Back of a length, around off. Dawid Malan blocks it to cover.
Flatter ball, turning down leg. Joe Root tucks it to the leg side for a run.
Nicely tossed up, on a length, around off and turning away late. Dawid Malan prods to block but leaves it alone in the end.
Flatter ball, on middle. Dawid Malan nudges it to the leg side and collects a single. That brings up the 100-run stand between Malan and Root!
Flatter ball, on a length, turning in late. Root waits for the ball to turn and turns it to wide of mid-wicket for a run.
Flatter ball, around off. Dawid Malan blocks it out.
Play and a miss! Flatter and quicker, outside off. Dawid Malan hangs back to cut but he misses as the ball spins past his outside edge.
LEG BYE! Back of a length ball, on the pads, Root stays back and looks to flick it away but misses. He gets hit just below the thigh pad and collects a leg bye as the ball rolls out.
Length and on off. Malan pushes it to cover and scampers through for a quick single.
Full length and outside off. Root steps forward and drives it past mid off. Head chases and does well to keep it down to a single.
Jhye Richardson comes 'round the wicket for the left-hander. On a length, on the fourth stump line. Malan hangs back and looks to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length and on the pads, Malan flicks it to mid-wicket and crosses for a single.
Full length and on off. Root leans in and drives it to cover. Not in the gap though.
Full and on off. Malan presses forward and defends it on the bounce to silly point.
Swing and a miss! So close! Flatter and short, outside off. Malan goes on the back foot and looks to cut it away but the ball sneaks past his outside edge.
Tossed up, full and on off. Malan prods and defends it out.
Looped up, full and on off. Malan blocks it out.
Flatter, angled onto the pads. Malan stays back and defends it to the leg side.
Fuller, on off. Malan drives it to cover but not in the gap though. First maiden for Nathan Lyon in 9 overs.
Fuller and on the pads, Root hangs back and clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Length and around off. Malan defends it to the off side without any hesitation.
A single now! On a length, around middle and leg. Dawid Malan flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played. Short ball, on the bodyline. Root swivels on the back foot and pulls it through square leg to bag a boundary.
OH BEAUTY! Good-length ball, around off. The ball nips in off the deck with some extra bounce. Root confidently shoulders his arms and trusts the bounce.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Root clips it to square leg but finds the fielder.
Good length and outside off, nips in late. Malan shoulders his arms at it.
Outside off, on a length, nipping in. Malan covers his stumps and shoulders his arms.

Hits the pad this time! A length ball, around off, nips away a bit. Malan puts his front leg forward and shoulders his arms. The ball rolls of the pads and goes behind. A stifled appeal but the umpire is not interested.
FOUR! Cracked! Back of a length, outside off. Malan stands tall and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller, on the pads, Malan clips it through mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Touch short and outside off. Root punches it through point off the back foot for a single. 6 runs off it.
Full length and on off. Root stays back and defends it out watchfully.

FOUR! Runs are coming in thick and fast for England now! A full-length ball, angled down leg. Root stays back and glances it towards fine leg for a boundary. This also brings up Root's 52nd Test fifty. His team needed such an innings from him. But the job is still half done and Root would look to convert this into three digits.
Good length, on top of off. Root defends it out.
Fuller and on off. Root stays inside the crease and blocks it out.
BEATEN! On a length, outside off, the ball straightens a bit after landing. Root presses forward, as he looks to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller, on the pads, Root clips it to fine leg and gets off the mark with a single,
Back of a length, around off. Root hops and guides it towards backward point for a run.
Another single now! Touch short and outside off. Malan pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full and on off. Root leans in and drives it through the diving fielder at cover. The batters take two runs comfortably.
Good length and outside off, Root shuffles across and leaves it alone.
Slightly short and on middle, Root swivels and pulls it to deep square leg. He rotates the strike.
On a length, outside off, angled in. Malan covers his stumps and leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good length, on off. Root stays back and defends it towards point.
Length, on fourth stump. Root defends it out.
On a length, on off. Root defends it to point.

LEG BYE! A full-length ball, around off. The ball stays low and nips in off the surface. Root hangs back and looks to flick it away but misses to get pinged on the pads. The batters collect a leg bye. Cameron Green appeals for lbw but the umpire is unmoved.
Length and on the pads, Malan blocks it out watchfully.
Back of a length, on off. Malan blocks it out solidly. THAT WILL BE DINNER ON DAY 3.
Full-length ball, around off. Root drives it towards mid off.
Length ball, on the stumps, at 135 kph. Joe Root blocks it out watchfully.
Good length, outside off. This one stays straight and Root shoulders his arms.
FOUR! Deft touch! Good length, on the fourth stump line. Root opens the face of the bat and plays it late. The ball sneaks through the slip cordon and into the fence at third man.
Length and on off. Root blocks it out watchfully.
On a length, on off. Root defends it to cover.
Uppish but safe! Floated, full and outside off. Malan chases it, the ball goes off the outer half towards point. It was in the air for a while, but lands short of the fielder.
Tossed up, full and outside off, Malan leaves it alone for the keeper. This is turns away a long way.
FOUR! Nicely played! First boundary now after the break for Malan. Short and outside off. Malan hangs back and cuts it through point for a boundary. He timed it to perfection.
Fuller, on off. Malan presses forward to defend it out.
Full and outside off. Malan prods and defends it towarrds gully off the outer half.
On off, Malan defends it out watchfully.
Full and on off. Root hangs back and blocks it to the off side.
Short, around middle and leg. Joe Root drags his pull shot towards fine leg and gets across for a single.
Good length and on off. Malan looks to pull it away but miscues as the ball comes off the top half of the blade.
On a length, outside off. Malan defends it to the slip cordon.
Back of a length, around the hips. Malan tucks it to mid-wicket for a single. 150 comes up for the visitors.
BEAUTY! Good-length ball, outside off, a bit extra bounce off  the deck. Root hangs back and looks to push it to the off side on the up, but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Full and on off. Malan presses forward and defends it into the deck.
Floated, full and on off. Malan drives it to cover.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Malan defends it out watchfully.
Full and on off. Malan gets forward and blocks it to silly point.
Short and outside off. Malan goes back and cuts it to point. The fielder moves to his left to stop the ball.
Second maiden of the innings for Lyon. Looped up, full and on off. Malan remains solid in his defense.

JAFFA! That is a peach of a delivery from Green! Good-length delivery, just outside off and nipping away a bit. Root looks to poke at it but the ball zips past his outside edge. Top stuff from Cameron Green!
On a length, around off. Joe Root blocks it out.
Fuller in length, outside off. Joe Root looks to drive but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards backward point.

OUT! CAUGHT! Cameron Green gets his reward and takes the big wicket of Joe Root! Green hurls a back-of-a-length delivery, around the corridor of uncertainty. Root looks to poke at it yet again and he gets a thick outside edge this time which goes straight to Australia's stand-in captain, Steven Smith at first slip who pouches it with ease. Root has to wait for his maiden Test hundred on Australian soil and this is a much-needed breakthrough for the hosts.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Cameron Green

Commentary: On a length, around off. Ben Stokes gets behind the line of the ball to block it.
Back of a length, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Tossed up, around off. Dawid Malan blocks it out.

Just short of the slip fielder! Loopy ball, on a length, outside off and spinning away. Dawid Malan looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and falls just in front of Steven Smith at first slip.
Flatter ball, outside off. Dawid Malan pushes it to backward point.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Dawid Malan stays back to cut but he misses.
On a length, outside off. Dawid Malan lets it be.
Tossed up, around off. Dawid Malan blocks it off the front foot.
Back of a length, on off. Ben Stokes hangs back to block this one out.
Short of a length, around off. Ben Stokes gets behind the line of the ball to defend it.
Play and a miss! Banged into the deck, outside off. Stokes gets low and looks to ramp it over the keeper but he fails to get any bat on it.
On a length, outside off and jagging back in. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around off. Ben Stokes blocks it back to the bowler.
A maiden over from Cameron Green! Good-length delivery, around off. Ben Stokes blocks it solidly.
Tossed up, outside off and spinning away late. Dawid Malan leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Another ball, on a length, outside off and turning away nicely. Malan prods but does not offer any shot to it.
Nicely tossed up, on a length, just outside off. Dawid Malan looks to defend at first but sways his bat away from the line in the end.
Looped up, on a length, on off. Dawid Malan blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Dawid Malan rocks back to cut but he misses.
On a length, around off. Malan gets solid in his defense this time around. Back-to-back maiden overs!
A low full toss, on off. Stokes drives it through mid on. The fielder there dives to his right and saves some runs for his side.
Back of a length, on off. Stokes keeps it out watchfully.
A yorker, around off. Ben Stokes squeezes it out nicely.
Green hurls a bumper, down leg. Stokes looks to pull but he fails to get any blade on it.
Uppish but safe! Fuller in length, outside off. Ben Stokes drives it towards the mid off fielder, on the bounce.
Fuller in length, around middle. Ben Stokes drives but straight to the mid on fielder.
Flighted, full and on off. Malan stays back and drives it to mid off.
Full and on the pads. Malan looks to flick it away. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards third man. The batters collect a brace.
Around off, pushed away to covers.
Tossed up, full and on off. Malan defends it on the front foot.

Floated, full and on off. Malan pushes it to cover and takes of for a single. The fielder collects the ball and has a shy at the non-striker's ned but spills it wide of the stumps. Malan gets inside the crease safely.
On off, blocked out solidly by Stokes.
EDGY! Fuller and on off. Malan puts his front leg across and looks to defend it but gets an inside edge and the ball sneaks through his leg and goes to the leg side.
Full length and on off. Malan digs it out on the bounce back to the bowler. Starc collects the ball and dummies a throw at Malan, who moves away from the stumps instantly.
Good length, just outside off, Malan leaves it alone and the ball brushes off the pads towards the keeper.
FOUR! Nicely played! A length ball, outside off. Malan cruches it behind point for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mitchell Starc comes back into the attack and strikes after getting hit for a boundary. He has the last laugh here. Back of a length, outside off. Malan looks to chase it away from his body. The ball goes off the outside edge towards Steven Smith at first slip, who pouches it safely to his right. Another set batter departs for the visitors. Have the floodgates opened up for the Aussies?
Howout: c Steven Smith b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Back of a length, down leg. Ollie Pope misses his flick and Alex Carey moves across to his left behind the sticks to gather the ball.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Excellent delivery! Flatter ball, on a length, around off and spinning away late. Ben Stokes looks to block but the ball zips past his outside edge.
On a length, around off. Stokes blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Ben Stokes pushes it to cover.
Tossed up, on a length, well outside off. Ben Stokes looks to sweep but the ball goes past his blade.
Another play and a miss! Flatter and quicker, outside off. Ben Stokes stays back to cut but the ball goes well over his outside edge. A maiden over from Lyon!
Good length, shaping across the right-hander. Pope prods and shoulders his arms.
Full length, on off. Pope pushes it to cover.
Three dots in a row! On a length, outside off. Pope plays it late and looks to steer it past gully. The man there dives to his right and makes a sharp stop.
A length ball, on off. Pope defends it to cover off the front foot.
A length ball, on the fourth stump line. Pope stays back and pushes it to point.

A single to end the over! Good running! Fuller and on off. Pope pushes it to the right of mid off with soft hands and calls for a single. The fielder moves to his right but is unable to gather the ball and attempt a shy at the non-striker's end. Pope dives to get inside the crease safely.
On off, Pope blocks it out solidly.
Fuller and on off. Pope remains solid in his defense.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Pope prods and defends it out solidly.
Flatter and on the pads, Pope goes back and tucks it to the leg side.
Short, outside off, Pope goes back and guides it towards short third man.
Angled into the batter, Pope goes back and keeps the ball out. Another maiden for Lyon, his sixth in this innings.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes shoulders his arms to this one.
Fuller in length, around off. Ben Stokes prods and drives it straight to the mid off fielder.
Length ball, darted on the pads. Ben Stokes flicks it to deep square leg and gets off the mark with a run. It took him 24 balls to get off the mark.
Good-length ball, on off. Ollie Pope blocks it to cover.

FOUR! Nicely played! Banged into the deck, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope sits back, swivels and pulls it behind square on the leg side. The fielder in the deep looks to cut it off but he fails to get down in time and concedes a boundary.
Length ball, on off. Ollie Pope pushes it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Tossed up, outside off and spinning away sharply. Stokes looks to block but the ball goes past his outside edge.
On a length, around off. Ben Stokes defends it off the front foot.
A bit quicker and flatter, outside off. Stokes rocks back and cuts it late past the backward point fielder for a single.

NOT OUT! A good review by Ollie Pope! This was nicely tossed up, around off and spinning in late. Pope looks to block but he misses and the ball hits his elbow and pops up towards short fine leg. Marnus Labuschagne takes the catch and Lyon appeals. The umpire raises his finger in no time. Pope reviews it and the RTS confirms that it came of Pope's elbow and not bat was involved.
Flatter ball, around off and spinning in late. Ollie Pope blocks it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Nathan Lyon gets his man this time and he is delighted! Lyon serves a full-length delivery outside off which turns in sharply. Pope skips down in order to smother the spin. He tries to flick but gets an inside edge. The ball pops up and goes towards Marnus Labuschagne at short leg who takes a good catch. Good quick reaction from Labuschagne. England sink further as they lose their fifth wicket now!
Howout: c Marnus Labuschagne b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Length ball, on off. Ben Stokes blocks it out.
Good-length delivery, around leg. Ben Stokes tucks it to fine leg and collects a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Jos Buttler shoulders arms to this one.
Good-length ball, on off. Jos Buttler prods and pushes it to cover.
BEATEN! Back of a length, around off and angling across the right-hander. Jos Buttler looks to poke at it but the ball zips past his outside edge.
Fuller in length, outside off. Jos Buttler drives but finds the cover fielder.
Flatter ball, on off. Ben Stokes stays back and pushes it to cover.
Another ball, shorter in length, around off. Ben Stokes gets back in his crease to block.
Flatter ball, on a length, around off. Ben Stokes blocks it to cover.
FOUR! Stokes breaks the shackles! This is a loopy ball, around off. Stokes gets down on his knee and sweeps it to the vacant deep square leg region for a boundary.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
On a length, around off and turning away a bit. Stokes defends it off the front foot.
Length ball, on middle. Jos Buttler tucks it to mid-wicket. Stokes looks for a run but is sent back by Buttler.
Length ball, way outside off. Jos Buttler prods and shoulders his arms to this one.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Jos Buttler leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Fuller in length, way outside off, inviting the right-hander to drive. Buttler accepts the invitation and looks for a booming drive but gets beaten on his outside edge.
Good-length ball, on off. Buttler looks to block but he gets a thick outside edge which rolls towards the gully fielder.
On a length, around off. Buttler prods and blocks it to cover.
Short, outside off, turning away. Stokes stays on the back foot and cuts it towards point.
Looped up, way outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Floated, around off. Stokes prods and defends it to silly point.
Flighted, full and on off. Stokes goes back and defends it out.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Stokes presses forward to block it out.
Another maiden for Lyon. Pressure continues to build on England. Short and wide outside off, Stokes stays on the back foor and cuts it square on the off side. Not in the gap though.
Fuller, just outside off. Buttler leans in and drives it to covers.
BEATEN! What a peach of a delivery. Good length, around off, shaping away from the batter. Jos Buttler looks to defend it but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Full and wide outside off. Buttler has no stroke to offer.
Length and wide outside off. Buttler leaves it alone.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mitchell Starc picks up his third wicket of the innings. Jos Buttler goes back without scoring. His first duck against Australia. The Aussies are dominating here. Starc enticed the batsman by going wide consistently and this time Buttler falls for it. Full-length ball, outside off, shaping away from the batter. Jos Buttler leans in and looks to drive it away. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the first slip. David Warner is stationed there who takes a brilliant catch.
Howout: c David Warner b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Good length and outside off. Woakes leaves it alone. A wicket-maiden for Mitchell Starc here.
Looped up, around off, Stokes shuffles across and flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Nice turn! Floated, outside off, on a length, it turns in a long way with some bounce. Woakes leaves it alone and gets pinged on the pads.
Quicker, angled down leg. Woakes leaves it alone.
Tossed up, wide outside off, Woakes leaves it alone.
Looped up, outside off, Woakes inside-edges it to mid-wicket,
Around off, turning in, Woakes blocks it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Stokes leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good length and wide of off. Stokes lets it sail past him.
Length and on the pads, Stokes defends it to the leg side.
On a length, around middle and off. Stokes defends it back to the bowler.
Good length, angled in on middle. Stokes shows full face of the bat and blocks it out.
Back of a length, on top of off. Stokes blocks it towards backward point for a single.
Floated, full and outside off, turning away. Stokes changes his stance and looks to reverse-sweep it but misses.
Looped up, around off, turns away sharply this time. Stokes leaves it alone.
Full and on off, Stokes prods and blocks it out.
Flatter and on off. Stokes defends it on the bounce to silly point.
Outside off, left alone by Stokes.
Flatter and on off. Stokes blocks it out watchfully.
Back of a length, around off. Chris Woakes blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Glorious! Fuller in length, outside off. Woakes prods and caresses it past the cover fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off. Chris Woakes looks to defend but it goes off the thick outside edge towards Steven Smith at second slip, on the bounce.
On a length, well outside off. Chris Woakes leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
BEATEN! Good-length ball, just outside off. Chris Woakes looks to poke at it but the ball whistles past his outside edge.
FOUR! EDGY! Good-length delivery, outside off. Chris Woakes stays back and looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge and sneaks through the second slip and the gully fielder for a boundary.
Flatter ball, on off. Ben Stokes blocks it out.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Ben Stokes does not offer any shot to thsi one.
Flatter ball, on off. Ben Stokes defends it off the front foot.
Loopy ball, on a length, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Flatter and quicker, on middle. Ben Stokes tucks it to the leg side.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Ben Stokes shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length, way outside off. Chris Woakes lets it be.
Short of a length, outside off. Chris Woakes lets it through to the keeper.
Good-length delivery, around off. Chris Woakes blocks it to cover.
FOUR! Nicely done! Fuller in length, outside off. Chris Woakes presses forward and drives it past the cover fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off. Chris Woakes taps it to backward point.
Uppish but safe! Length ball, outside off. Chris Woakes looks to drive but it goes off the outside half of the blade towards the backward point fielder.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Ben Stokes looks to defend but the ball spins and hits him on his thigh pad.
Fuller in length, around middle. Ben Stokes clips it past mid on and takes a run.
Flatter ball, turning down leg. Chris Woakes tucks it behind square on the leg side for a run.
Flatter ball, around off. Ben Stokes blocks it out.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Ben Stokes looks to block but it goes off the outside edge past the diving slip fielder for a couple of runs.
On a length, around off. Ben Stokes defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length, around leg. Chris Woakes nudges it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! SHOT! Fuller in length, outside off. Woakes presses forward and carves it through the cover region for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Chris Woakes defends it off the back foot.
On a length, outside off. Chris Woakes drives it past the cover fielder and the batters take a couple of runs.
FOUR! What a shot! Chris Woakes is on the charge! Banged into the deck, around off. Woakes hangs back and pulls it in front of square past the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary.
Short of a length, outside off. Chris Woakes lets it be.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Floated, on a length, on middle. Ben Stokes defends it off the front foot.
Loopy ball, on a length, around middle. Ben Stokes blocks it out solidly.
Flatter ball, on a length, around middle. Ben Stokes gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it.
Flatter ball, on a length, outside off. Ben Stokes stays back and pushes it to cover.
Lyon serves a full ball, around middle. Ben Stokes digs it out and loses his balance and also the bat in the process. That will be Tea on Day 3!
Neser starts with a shorter ball, wide outside off. Woakes goes at it with his hands but misses.
Fired full and on middle. Woakes looks to flick it away but gets the leading edge back to the bowler.
Beaten! This lands on a length, just outside off. Woakes looks to block from the crease but it zips past the outside edge.
On a length, around off. Woakes gets the outside edge past gully for one.
Fuller and right on the off pole. Stokes blocks it right under his eyes.
Full and on the pads. Stokes flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flatter, lands on middle and turns down the leg side. Left alone.
Wrong line again. Around off and turns down the leg side again.
Shorter ball, lands outside off and comes back in. Nicely blocked by Woakes.
Woakes comes down the track and works it nicely to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, outside off. Woakes blocks it well.
Short of a length, outside off. Stokes blocks it from the crease.
Nicely driven through covers for a couple.
Length ball, around off. Blocked out.
Another solid defence by Stokes.
Short of a length, around off. Stokes works it past mid-wicket for one.
Length ball, around off. Woakes blocks it from the crease.
Full and on off. Stokes drives it to deep cover for one.
Loopy ball, on off, it comes back in. Woakes stays solid in his defence.
Sharp turn! Lands outside off and comes back in. Woakes goes back to block but gets hit on the thigh pads.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Woakes whips it towards mid on along the ground.
OUT! BOWLED! Snorter! Shorter and lands outside off. This comes back in sharply. Woakes looks to block but it goes off the inside edge and the stumps are shattered!
Howout: b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Tossed up, outside off. Robinson comes forward to block it.
Back of a length, around off. Ben Stokes stays back and blocks it past covers for a run.
Fuller in length, angling in from off. Ollie Robinson defends it off the front foot.
BEATEN! Good-length ball, around off and nipping away late. Robinson looks to poke at it but the ball zips past his outside edge.
On a length, around off. Ollie Robinson blocks it to cover.

DROPPED! Back of a length, outside off. Ollie Robinson looks to push it on the up on the off side but he gets a thick outside edge and the ball goes towards Mitchell Starc at gully who drops it. The ball pops up and goes towards Steven Smith at second slip. Smith looks to grab it with his right hand but he fails to gather it. Robinson survives.
Back of a length, outside off. Ollie Robinson looks to heave it away but he fails to get any bat on it.
Full and on off, pushed to cover.
Full and on off, kept it out.
Full and on off. Stokes pushes it to deep point for a single.

OUT! LBW! Nathan Lyon gets his third wicket and England are in deep trouble now! Flatter ball, outside off and spinning in sharply. Robinson is stuck to his crease and looks to flick it across the line. He misses it and gets pinged on his pad. Lyon appeals and the umpire raises his finger. Robinson reviews straightaway! The Hawk Eye suggests that the impact is umpire's call and the wickets hitting. Robinson has to take the long walk back to the pavilion.
Howout: lbw b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Flatter ball, on off. Stuart Broad blocks it out.
Turn and bounce! Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Stuart Broad looks to defend but the ball goes past his outside edge.
Short of a length, on off. Flicked to mid-wicket..
FOUR! Lucky boundary! Like we said, Stokes could cut loose now! Length ball, on off. Stokes looks to heave it away but gets the inside edge. It runs to the fine leg fence.
Driven to long off but a single is not taken.
Short of a length, outside off. Stokes cuts it to covers.
Short and on off. Stokes lets it go.
Short ball, outside off. Stokes ramps it to third man for one.
Short and outside off. Cut away to deep cover. Single is not taken.
Loopy ball, around off. Stokes gets the outside edge but it drops short of second slip.
SIX! All the way! We could be in for a T20-style game now! Tossed up, on off. Stokes gets low and slog-sweeps it over the mid-wicket fence.
Shorter ball, around off. Pushed to covers.
FOUR! Up and over! Tossed up, outside off. Stokes backs away and goes heaves it over mid off for a boundary.
Stokes flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.

Short and outside off. Stokes slams it to the left of deep point. Harris gets across and dives to stop it. His knee gets stuck in the ground and he has an awkward. Stokes has a surprised look after seeing that.
Stokes looks to go downtown but gets it towards deep square leg.

OUT! BOWLED! Green does the trick! Stokes really had no other option but to attack now! Green bowls it short of a length and outside off. Stokes looks to slog it away but gets the inside edge. The ball goes back to hit the stumps and England's chances of avoiding the follow on are dismal now.
Howout: b Cameron Green

Commentary: Short of a length, outside off. Anderson looks to block but is beaten.
Short of a length, around off. Pushed to point for one.
Length ball, around off. Broad looks to block but gets the toe end towards first slip.
Massive bounce and swing! Back of a length, way outside off, shaping away. James Anderson looks to chase it but misses.
Back of a length, on off, close to the body. James Anderson hops and defends it out.
BEATEN! Shapes away nicely. Good-length ball, around off. The ball nips away off the deck. James Anderson looks to defend it out but gets beaten at the outside edge.
Short and on off. The ball flies off the deck. James Anderson hangs back and defends it out solidly.
Good-length ball, outside off. James Anderson looks to have a poke at it but pulls his blade back eventually. The ball zips past the outside edge.
A maiden for Mitchell Starc. Length and on off. James Anderson blocks it out watchfully.
NASTY!! That must've hurt. Short ball, on the bodyline. Stuart Broad hops and looks to defend it out. The ball goes of his gloves and hits the grill on its way.
Back of a length, on the bodyline. Stuart Broad hops inside the crease and defends it out to the leg side.
Another short delivery, on the bodyline. Stuart Broad blocks it to short leg.
Back of a length, around middle, shaping away. Stuart Broad leaves it alone.

TWO LEG BYES! Short ball, on the body. Broad jumps and leans back in the process. The ball goes off the arm over Alex Carey to fine leg. The batters collect a couple of runs, as the fielder takes some time to get to the ball.
Back of a length, around leg. Stuart Broad hangs back and clips it past short leg for a single.
Sharp bumper, arouund middle and leg. Stuart Broad sways away from the line of the delivery.
Short ball, around off. Stuart Broad stays back and looks to heave it away but misses.
Short ball, around middle and leg. Broad leans back and leaves it alone.
Fuller, on the pads, Stuart Broad clips it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Slightly short, on middle and off. Anderson shuffles across and defends it solidly.
