OH, Well bowled. Got too much curve on it this time. Fuller, around off, shaping away. James Anderson looks to dig it out but gets beaten by the shape.

SIX! BANG! Mitchell Starc holds the catch on the ropes. He has a big smile on his face. Stuart Broad gets lucky and gets his 50th Test match six of his career. Back of a length ball, around middle and leg. Stuart Broad looks to hook it away. The ball takes the outside edge and flies towards fine leg. Mitchell Starc grabs the ball safely only to realise he has stepped on the ropes, as he tumbles on the ground.
Banged in a short ball, on off. Broad leaves it alone.
Short and on off. Stuart Broad pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
A length ball, angled into the batter. James Anderson looks to defend it out but gets banged on the pads.
Length ball, angled into the batter again. James Anderson looks to defend it out but misses to get hit just under the box. He would be glad.
FOUR! Nicely played! Full length and on off. James Anderson shuffles across and clips it through square leg to bag a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! England are bowled out for 236. Stuart Broad looks to go downtown but miscues his hit. Mitchell Starc gets his fourth wicket of the game. Touch short, around middle and leg. Broad moves back and looks to heave it away. The ball flies towards cover off the outer half. Head settles under it and takes it easily. 50 wickets in Day-Night Tests for Mitchell Starc. ENGLAND TRAIL BY 237 RUNS.
Howout: c Travis Head b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Anderson starts with a length ball, outside off and angling across the batter. David Warner leaves it alone.
A touch fuller this time, around the fifth stump line. Warner sways away from the line of the delivery.
Another ball, on a length, around the same channel. Warner does not offer any shot to this one.

FOUR LEG BYES! This one came back in sharply! Good-length ball, around middle and jagging back in late. Warner hops in his crease to block but he misses and gets hit high on his pad. The ball ricochets off his pads and races away past the keeper and into the fence.
On a length, around off. Dawid Malan stays back and blocks it out.
Back of a length, way outside off. David Warner lets it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, outside off. David Warner shoulders his arms to it.
On a length, angling down leg. Marcus Harris misses his flick.
Short of a length, jagging back in from off. Marcus Harris looks to block but he misses and gets hit on his thigh pad.
Good-length delivery, around off. Marcus Harris defends it solidly off the front foot.
First runs off the bat! Length ball, darted on the pads. Harris clips it behind square on the leg side for a couple of runs.
Fuller in length, outside off and curling away a touch. Harris leaves it alone.
Length ball, outside off. David Warner leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Short of a length, around middle. David Warner hangs back and blocks it towards backward point.
Lovely delivery! Fuller in length, angling across the left-hander. Warner looks for a drive without any feet movement and gets beaten on his outside edge.
Short of a length, around off. David Warner blocks it to point.
This is a bit fuller, around middle. Warner gets solid in his defense.
Length ball, around the hips. Warner glances it behind square on the leg side and takes a couple of runs.
Good-length ball, around middle. Marcus Harris tucks it to mid-wicket.
Full ball, outside off. Harris prods to block but he gets a thick outside edge towards the gully fielder, on the bounce.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. Harris nudges it towards deep square leg for a single.
Full-length ball, outside off. Warner drives but Dawid Malan at covers does well to stop it by diving to his left.
Short of a length, jagging back in from middle. David Warner stays back to block but he misses and the ball hits him high on his body.
On a length, around middle and leg. David Warner stays back and tucks it to wide of mid on. He gets off the mark with a couple of runs.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. Harris gets on top of the bounce and tucks it to the leg side for a run.
Good running! Good-length ball, on middle. Warner hops in his crease and turns it to wide of mid on for a brace.
A bit shorter this time, outside off. Marcus Harris leaves it alone.
Back of a length, angling across the left-hander from outside off. Marcus Harris does not offer any shot to it.
On a length, well outside off. Harris lets it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, outside off. Marcus Harris leaves it alone watchfully.

Good length, outside off, this one seams back in. David Warner looks to defend it out but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad. Stuart Broad makes a stifled appeal and the umpire is unmoved. Joe Root is seen saying, 'Go fuller, go fuller'.
FOUR! Nicely played! On a length, outside off. Warner drives it nicely to the cover fence. Good shot that.
Lands outside off and comes back in on a length. Warner looks to block but gets hit on the pads.
On a length, around off. Pushed to covers.
Length ball, on off. Worked to the leg side.
Fuller and outside off. Warner comes forward and blocks it.
On a length, just outside off. Harris is aware of where his off pole and misses.
Length ball, on off. Harris blocks it out.
A touch fuller, on the fifth-stump line. Harris comes forward and blocks it.
Short of a length, on off. Harris goes back and blocks it.
A touch fuller, around off. Harris covers the hint of away shape and blocks it.
Length ball, wide enough for Harris to leave it with ease.
Full and on off. Warner blocks it from the crease.

NO BALL! Length ball, on off. Warner pushes it to the left of the bowler. Robinson puts his left hand out but cannot stop it. It goes down the ground and a couple of runs are taken. Oh, it is also called a no ball as Robinson has overstepped!
Short of a length, outside off. Warner pushes it past covers for one.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! Lovely stroke! Full and on the pads. Harris nicely flicks it to the square leg fence.
Short of a length, around off. Harris looks to block but gets hit on the pads.

Appeal for LBW! Fuller ball, around leg. Harris looks to block but gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but not given. Root has a word with Robinson but the English skipper thinks that it was pitching outside leg.
Length ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Length ball, just outside off. Warner covers the stumps and leaves it.
On a length, on middle. Warner works it past square leg for one.
Length ball, around off. Harris looks to block but gets the inside edge past square leg for a couple.
Harris gets the inside edge past square leg again while looking to block. A couple of runs again.
FOUR! Nicely played! Shorter ball, outside off. Harris goes back and cuts it past covers for a boundary.

It would have been curtains for Warner had the fielder hit that! Length ball, on off. Warner taps it towards mid-wicket and sets off for a single. Woakes goes for it and fires a throw at the bowler's end but misses the stumps. Warner would have been out by a mile there!
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
On a length, right on the off pole. Harris offers the full face of the bat and blocks it.
On a length, on the pads. Harris looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad. The ball drops down near his feat.
Length ball, angling across off. Harris leaves it alone.
Short of a length, around off. Harris works it past square leg for one.
BEATEN! Good length, angled across the left-hander. Harris looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Back of a length, outside off. Harris shoulders his arms to it.
BEAUTY! Another good delivery from Chris Woakes. On a length, around off, shaping away. Harris presses forward but fails to defend it out.
FOUR! UP AND OVER! Short ball, wide outside off. Marcus Harris stays back and chases this one. The ball goes over the slip cordon off the outside edge and into the fence at third man.
A length ball, on off. Harris blocks it out.
On a length, around off. Harris blocks it out solidly.
A length ball, outside off, shaping away. David Warner leaves it alone.
Length and angling across, Warner leaves it alone.
Fuller in length, just outside off. Warner comes forward and blocks it.
On a length, around off. Warner goes back and blocks it.
Length ball, just outside off. Warner gets forward and blocks it.
Length ball, on the off pole. Warner blocks it from the crease.
Full length, outside off. Harris presses forward and blocks it out solidly.
Back of a length, around off. Harris covers his stumps and shoulders his arms. Trusting the bounce this time.
Nice leave! On a length, around off, Harris shuffles across and shoulders his arms.
Full and on off. Harris comes across and defends it out.
Fuller, on the pads. Harris clips it to the leg side.
Good length, angling across the batter. Harris looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Looped up, full and on off. David Warner defends it into the deck.
Turn and bounce! Flatter ball, on a length, around off and turning away. David Warner looks to block but the ball spins past his blade.
Flatter ball, on middle. David Warner tucks it to the leg side and rotates the strike by taking a run.
Fuller in length, around off. Marcus Harris defends it out.
Tossed up, on a length, around middle. Marcus Harris blocks it off the front foot.

OUT! RUN OUT! Oh dear! Absolute chaos in the middle and it is David Warner who has to walk back to the pavilion! This was a flatter ball, on leg. Marcus Harris tucks it to square leg and takes off for a run. Warner at the non-striker's end is in two minds whether to run or not and by the time he goes for it he was halfway down the pitch and Stuart Broad had thrown the ball to Jos Buttler. So Warner decides to run back to the bowler's end but Harris had already reached the non-striker's end and the former pulls out in the end. Buttler whips the bails off and Warner takes the long walk back to the hut. To be honest, Warner has sacrificed his wicket here. If he wished, he could have scampered back to the non-striker's end and made it in before Harris. But he knew that it was his call and hence, his mistake, so did not bother to put in too much effort once he saw Harris fully committed. Team spirit.
Howout: run out (Stuart Broad / Jos Buttler)

Commentary: Full-length ball, on off. Marcus Harris closes the face of the bat early and works it towards short mid on.
Short and wide outside off. Harris punches it towards point.
Good length, angled across the batter. Marcus Harris leaves it alone.
Another one, wide of off. Harris leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around off, shaping away. Marcus Harris stays back and shoulders his arms.
Fuller and on off. Harris presses forward and works it to mid-wicket. A maiden for Woakes now.
Back of a length, outside off, nips in late. Michael Neser hangs back and shoulders his arms.

BEATEN! Nicely bowled. On a length, around off, nips away off the deck. Michael Neser looks to defend it out. The ball brushes his gloves and goes towards third man through the keeper. The batters collect two leg byes.
Michael Neser is off the mark now! Full length, on off. Michael Neser looks to drive it through cover. The ball takes the outer half and  goes through point. The batters take a couple.
Good length, outside off, shaping away. Michael Neser leaves it alone.
On a length, around off, Michael Neser leaves it alone.
Full length, outside off. Michael Neser works it to covers.
Floated, full and outside off. Marcus Harris leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Bounce and turn this time. Flighted, full and outside off. Marcus Harris prods and looks to defend it out. The ball grips and turns away to zip past the outside edge.
Full and on off. Harris blocks it out watchfully.
Fuller and on middle. Harris pushes it out off the inner half.
Floated, full and on off. Harrish pushes it to silly point.
Outside off, Harris cuts it towards point. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 3.

NOT OUT! Length ball, on the fourth stump line. Michael Neser leans and pushes it towards point. Haseeb Hameed stops the ball. Michael Neser starts running but is sent back by his partner. He has a shy at the striker's end and scores a direct it. Michael Neser dives to make it back. They take the single off the overthrows. Meanwhile, England appeal for a run out. It is sent upstrairs and the replay shows that Neser's strecth had saved him.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Harris turns it on the leg side.
Good-length ball, down leg. Marcus Harris tries to flick but misses.
Fuller in length, around off. Marcus Harris leans forward and blocks it on the off side.
Fuller in length again, coming back in. Harris flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Good-length ball, on off. Harris blocks it out.
Fuller, outside off. Neser watches the ball closely and makes a leave.
Good-length ball, on off. Neser punches it towards covers off the back foot.
Good-length ball, on middle. Neser covers the line and blocks it from the crease.
Good-length ball, coming back in, on off. Neser leaves it alone.
An action replay of the previous delivery. Neser lets it be.

OUT! TIMBER! The nightwatchman has been sent packing! Just the start England needed. Anderson bowls a good-length delivery, on off, coming back in. Michael Neser presses forward to defend. The ball nips back in enough to get past Neser's defence and shatters the wooden furniture behind him.
Howout: b James Anderson

Commentary: Length ball, from 'round the wicket, on middle. Harris defends it out.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! This is what England need! They needed early wickets and England's two frontline pacers are just doing that job. This time it is Broad who gets it. He bowls a good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away. Marcus Harris has a poke at it. The ball goes off the outside edge and flies through to the keeper. Jos Buttler took a brilliant catch in the first innings and it was of Harris and this time it is Harris again. Buttler dives to his left and takes a one-handed stunner. Brilliant from the keeper and England have got two wickets in quick succession.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Stuart Broad

Commentary: DROPPED! Can you believe it? Another good-length ball, around off, nipping away. Steven Smith tries to work it on the off side. The ball goes off the outside edge and goes to the keeper. Jos Buttler dives to his right but fails to pouch it. This could prove costly as they could have had Steven Smith for a duck. The ball hit him under his palms, missed by a fraction. A second ago Jos Buttler was the hero, but a second later Jos Buttler back to being the culprit. This was easier than the catch of Harris. Hope this does not get the heads down in the field for the visitors.

NOT OUT! Good-length ball, on off, coming back in. Smith looks to defend but misses. He gets rapped on the pads. England appeal for an lbw but the umpire says no. They take a review. UltraEdge shows no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows that it was umpire's call on wickets hitting. England retain their review and Steven Smith survives.
This is blocked on the off side.
Length ball, going down leg. Steven Smith looks to flick but misses. An end of an eventful over.
Good-length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it sail through.
Back of a length, outside off, nipping in. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms to that one.
Good-length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it untouched.
Another length delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms.
On a good length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne continues his leaving spree.
Good-length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go. A maiden for James Anderson!
Fuller in length, on off. Smith drives it but straight to short cover.
Good-length ball, coming back in, on middle. Steven Smith covers the line and blocks it out.
Fuller again, on middle. Smith nudges it to mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, outside off. Smith shoulders arms to that one.
FOUR! Shot! Fuller this time, on off. Steven Smith drives it through covers. The fielder gives it a chase but no chance stopping that and he collects a boundary. Gets off the mark as well.
On a good length, outside off. Smith lets it be.
Good-length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it sail through.
On a length, coming back in, around off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Good-length ball, on leg, nipping back in. Marnus Labuschagne tries to defend but the ball keeps low and hit him on the pads.
On a good length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne plays it back to the bowler.
OUCH! That must have hurt! Good-length ball, on middle. The ball shoots up after hitting the deck. Marnus Labuschagne turns away and gets hit on the ribs.
Good-length ball, on middle and off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it out.
Length delivery, outside off. Steven Smith leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Steven Smith leans and trives to drive it on the up. The ball sneaks past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
Much fuller, on middle. Smith nudges it on the leg side.
Fuller, outside off. Steven Smith shoulders arms.
Length ball, on off. Steven Smith defends it out.
Fuller, outside off. Steven Smith lets it sail through.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms to that one.
Fuller in length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to short cover.
On a good length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to point.
Fuller in length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne presses forward and blocks it out.
Back of a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne hops and tucks it on the leg side for a single.
On a good length, outside off. Steven Smith lets it through to the keeper.
On a good length, on off, angling in. Marnus Labuschagne watchfully blocks it out.
Back of a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out from the crease.
Fuller, outside off. Left alone.
Back of a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne jumps and defends it back to the bowler.
On a good length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne is solid in his defence.
On a good length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out.
Good-length ball, outside off, nipping in. Smith shoulders arms.
On a length, down leg. Steven Smith works it to fine leg for a single.
On a good length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it through.
Good-length ball, outside off, coming back in. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms to that one.
Outside off, Marnus Labuschagne lets it be.
Fuller in length, on off, driven to covers.
On a good length, outside off. Steven Smith shoulders arms.
Beaten! Good-length delivery, on off, nipping away. Steven Smith prods and looks to defend. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Fuller, on off, driven towards covers.
Fuller again, on middle. Steven Smith defends it nicely on the leg side.
Good-length ball, outside off. Steven Smith lets it go.
Fuller in length, on off. Pushed to wide of mid off for a single.
Fuller in length, outside off. Steven Smith leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on off. Steven Smith defends it on the leg side.
On a good length, on middle. Steven Smith tucks it to square leg.
A bumper, on middle and leg. Steven Smith sways away from the line and lets it go.
Back of a length, on off. Steven Smith stands tall and blocks it out from the crease.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! That is a very good catch from Jos Buttler. He has put down a couple of catches in this Test match but has taken some spectacular ones as well. This was back-of-a-length ball, on middle. Steven Smith has a habit of moving a little to the off side to play the ball. He does so again and tries to work it on the leg side. The ball goes off the gloves to the keeper. Jos Buttler dives full stretch to his left and grabs another one-handed catch. Excellent stuff from him and England have got the Aussie skipper.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Fuller, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it out.
Short of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms.
Fuller in length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to drive but gets beaten.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it on the leg side.
On a good length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne knocks it back to the bowler.
Short ball, on middle. Travis Head ducks under it.
Short of a length, outside off, angling away. Travis Head has a feel for it. The ball whizzes past the outside edge. Extra bounce on that occasion as well.
Back of a length, on middle. Head blocks it out.
Length ball, on off. Travis Head defends it off the front foot.
On a good length, from 'round the wicket, on off. Travis Head blocks it to the off side.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Back of a length, outside off. Travis Head hops and punches it through covers for a boundary. A nice way to open the account.
On a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne hangs back and defends it back to the bowler.
Labuschagne remians solid in his defense. A length ball, on off stumps. Defended out solidly.
Length, angled on the pads, Marnus Labuschagne stays back and flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Second boundary of the innings for Travis Head. Touch short, around off. Head gets into the position early and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length and around off. Head stays back and defends it to the right of point.
Full length and on off. Head presses forward and defends it on the bounce to mid off. Good over by Woakes.
Good length, around off, nips in a little late. Marnus Labuschagne stays inside the crease and shoulders his arms to it.
Back of a length, on off, close to the body. Marnus Labuschagne hangs back, opens the face of the bat late and guides it to the slip cordon.
BEATEN! On a length, in the corridor of uncertainty. Marnus Labuschagne hangs his blade out to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
A fancy leave by Marnus Labuschagne. Short and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne shuffles across and leaves it alone.
FOUR! First boundary for Marnus Labuschagne after 41 deliveries. Fuller, on middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne stays inside the crease and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries. Good use of the wrists yet again. Full length, on leg. Marnus Labuschagne hangs back and clips it in front of leg for a boundary.

FOUR! Nicely played. Fourth boundary for Australia off the last 10 deliveries. Woakes goes full and outside off, Head goes back and creams it through the cover region for a boundary. England need to remain full, but not overpitch the ball, a few boundaries shouldn't harm.
Full length and on off. Travis Head punches it through cover. Ollie Pope dives to his left and gets a hand on it, which kills the pace of the ball. The batters take a brace.
A length ball, angled into the pads, Head looks to flick it away but misses and gets pinged on the pads. Chris Woakes appeals for lbw but the umpire is unmoved. Going down leg maybe.
Much better from Woakes. Goes short and outside off this time. The ball nips in off the deck. Travis Head shoulders his arms to it. This was a close leave.
Fuller and on middle. Head flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Good length and wide of off pole. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it to point.
Flighted, full and outside off. Head leaves it alone. This one turns a bit.
Tossed up, around off. Head pushes it to the left of the bowler on a bounce. Ollie Robinson goes to his left and grabs the ball.
Full and on off. Head defends it out.
Full and on off. Head pushes it to cover.
Floated, full and on off. Head pushes it to mid off for a single.
Full and on off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to mid off for another single. A good over by Ollie Robinson, with his off spin.
JAFFA! Good length and around off, nips away off the deck. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Another beauty by Woakes. On a length, around off, shaping away off the deck. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend it out but misses. This time the ball zips past the outside edge.
Fuller and on off. Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it out solidly.
Another ripper from Woakes. On a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! Nicely played. A good end to the over for Australia. Full and on leg. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
Tossed up, full and on off. Head defends it out.
Short and on off. Head stays back and cuts it through cover-point for a brace.
Tossed up, on off, Head drives it to mid off and rotates the strike.
Around middle, Marnus Labuschagne works it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to mid off.
Length and on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it to mid off. He wanted a single but was sent back by Head.
A length ball, angled across the left-hander, on middle. Travis Head blocks it solidly.
Good length, on off. Head remains solid in his defense.
On the pads, Head defends it out to the leg side.
Four dots on the trot! Touch short and on off. Head hangs back and defends it back to the bowler.
A single now! Short, around the hips. Head clips it to square leg for a single.
Length and on off. Marnus Labuschagne works it to point off the outer half.
Fuller and on off. Head flicks it towards mid on and gets a single.
Short and on the pads, Marnus Labuschagne clips it to fine leg for a single.
Full and on middle. Head comes down the track and works it towards mid on for a single. These are easy runs for Australia.
Very full and on leg. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to square leg for a run.
Tossed up, full and on off. Head works it to mid on for another run.
Full toss and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne reaches out and slashes it towards sweeper cover for another single.
Good length, wide outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.

FOUR! EDGY! Just wide of Root at first slip. Back of a length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne keeps the blade close to his body. The ball takes the outside edge and goes past the attempt of Root for a boundary. Joe Root still looks to be in some kind of pain. Maybe he was a bit hesitant before diving for the catch. Bizarre, bizarre captaincy - whoever it be - Ben Stokes or Joe Root. You can place two slips for Chris Woakes - but when your best bowlers of the afternoon are bowling - Anderson and Broad - you have one slip. Why this partiality? Even though Australia have a big lead, if England can stop them under 150, who knows, we may be in for a miracle. For that, they need wickets.
On off, defended out.
Back of a length, outside off, nips in late. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms.
BEATEN! Good length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne gets squared up as he looks to defend it out and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short and outside off, nips away a bit. Marnus Labuschagne is happy to leave that one alone.
Short and on off. Head pulls it through mid-wicket for a single. 100 comes up for Australia.
Slightly short and on off. Marnus Labuschagne swivels and pulls it to deep square leg for a single. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.
Short and outside off. Head cuts it to cover-point but straight to the fielder.
Back of a length, around the hips. Head tucks it to square leg for a single.
NO BALL! Second no ball off the over, as Ben Stokes oversteps. Length and on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it out watchfully.
Length, around off, nipping in. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket for a single. The stand moves to 50.
WIDE! A sharp bouncer, around leg. Head ducks under this one and the umpire signals a wide.
FOUR! This is tunring out to be a big over for Australia. Slightly short and on off. Head stays back and pulls it through square leg for a boundary.
Length and on the pads, Head flicks it to mid-wicket for a single. 12 runs coming off it. Ben Stokes should aim going full, rather than continuing with his short ball ploy.
Good length and angled into the pads, Head stays back and flicks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Full length and on off. Marnus Labuschagne gets it off the outer half aerially towards point. But the ball lands in front of the fielder.
Good length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone for the keeper.
Touch short and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms at it.

Play and a miss! This has happened a several times today for England. A length ball, around off, nips away off the deck sharply. Marnus Labuschagne looks to drive it through the cover region but gets beaten.
Touch short and on off. Marnus Labuschagne drags his pull shot to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Smacked! Short and outside off. Head hangs back and pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary. The lead moves to 353 for Australia.
Fuller, on off. Head clips it to mid-wicket.
Length, around middle and off. Head defends it back to the bowler. Another no ball by Stokes, this is his third in two overs.

Marnus Labuschagne is just home! The dive save him though. Full and on the pads. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to deep square leg. Ollie Pope comes out with a nice effort near the ropes to save the boundary. He throws it flat towards the keeper. Jos Buttler collects it well and removes the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne dives and gets himself insde the crease safely and the replays suggest the same, as the umpire takes it upstairs.
On off, defendedout watchfully.
FOUR! Runs are coming in thick and fast for the hosts. Short ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne stands back and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone by Marnus Labuschagne.
FOUR! In the gap, timed to perfection. Length ball, on the pads. Head flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
Short of a length, outside off. Travis Head pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Good length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone for the keeper.
Fuller and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and clips it through mid-wicket for three runs.
Aggressive running here! Touch short, on leg. Head clips it to fine leg. Travis Head calls for two and gets two runs.
Length and on off. Travis Head defends it to cover.

Nice work by Ollie Pope in the field. A length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne hangs back and punches it through cover-point. The ball races away past the diving attempt of the fielder. Ollie Pope gives it a chase and slides foward to pull the ball back in play. Save a run for his side here, as the batters run three.
Good-length ball, on off. Travis Head blocks it out to cover.
Length ball, around leg. Head stays back and looks to flick it away but misses. The ball meets the keeper on the bounce to his left. Comes off the hips this time.
Angled into the pads, Head looks to nudge it to the leg side but misses.
FOUR! Top shot! A full-length ball, on off. Head hits it past the bowlers head and into the fence at long off.
TWO RUNS! FIFTY for Travis Head. He is scoring for fun here. Short ball, on off. Head pulls it through mid-wicket for a brace.
On a good length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to point for a single.
Full and outside off. Head throws his bat at it and gets an inside edge towards mid on.
Fuller and on off. Head digs it out back to the bowler.
SWING AND A MISS! Length ball, outside off, angled across the left-hander. Travis Head stays on the back foot and looks to cut it away but misses.
Length and on off. Head defends it out watchfully.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ben Stokes takes a stunning catch in the deep to send back Travis Head. His entertaining innings comes to an end. Ollie Robinson picks up his second wicket and breaks an important partnership this time. Short ball, around off. Head stays back and thinks of riding the bounce. He hooks to deep square leg. Ben Stokes runs to his left and takes a good low diving catch to his left. He gets there in time.
Howout: c Ben Stokes b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: A dot now! Good length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it to the leg side.
On a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it to the off side and rotates the strike.

OH DEAR! Marnus Labuschagne was a goner here. A length ball, outside off. Cameron Green shuffles across and defends it to backward point. He hesitates for a single and Marnus Labuschagne was late in his charge to the danger end. Ollie Pope collects the ball and has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Marnus Labuschagne had given up and way not anywhere near the popping crease.
A length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne guides it towards backward point for a brace.
Good length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend it out but misses.
Full and on leg, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it through square leg for a single.
Ollie Robinson goes past the outside edge another time! Length ball, landing on off and nipping away. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend it out but misses.
FOUR! Up and over! Full-length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne walks down the pitch and lofts it over mid on to bag a boundary. 150 is up for Australia. The lead moves to 390.
Length and on the pads, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller and on off. Green tucks it towards mid on for another single.
A dot now! Full length, on the pads, Marnus Labuschagne clips it to short mid-wicket.
Play and a miss! Short ball, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne looks to hook it away but misses.
Full length, on middle and leg. Green shuffles across and flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Good length, on off. Green blocks it out watchfully.
Fuller and outside off, Green coves his stumps and defends it out to cover.
Length ball, around off, nips is a bit. Green shuffles across and helps it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, Green leans in and drives it towards cover-point.
Good length, on top of off. Green comes across yet again and defends it to the leg side.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne nudges it on the leg side for a single.
Length ball, on middle. Cameron Green tucks it to square leg for a run.
Short of a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne slaps it to deep cover for a single.
NO BALL! Short ball, on middle. Cameron Green lets it be. Ollie Robinson oversteps and the umpire signals a no ball.
On a length, on middle. Cameron Green works it to deep square leg for a brace. Australia now lead by 400 runs!
Fuller in length, on middle. Pushed to mid off.
On a good length, on off. Cameron Green blocks it out.
Short and on off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it to point for a single.
Full and around leg, Green goes back and flicks it to square leg for a run now.
Tossed up, around off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to point for a single.
A dot now! Flatter and around off. Green works it towards point.
On off, defended out.
Floated and on middle. Green defends it to the leg side. A good over by Malan.
Full length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it firmly through cover for a single.
Length and on leg. Green tucks it behind square for a single.
Length and on the pads, Marnus Labuschagne clips it to the leg side for a single. FIFTY up for Marnus Labuschagne. He truly enjoys batting against England.
Fuller, on off. Green pushes it to cover. Haseeb Hameed misfields, the batters were looking for a single, but Hameed was quick to rectify his mistake and restricts a single here.
Full and on off. Malan drives it through covers for a brace now.
Full and on the pads, Green nudges it to mid-wicket.
Floated, full and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Around off, Green pushes it to cover for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Dawid Malan gets his first Test wicket and this is only the third time Marnus Labuschagne slipped out to a leg-spinner. Floated, full and on off. Marnus Labuschagne gets low and slog-sweeps it to deep mid-wicket. He does not get the desired distance on it and Ben Stokes will never drop such sitters. He pouches it comfortably and Marnus Labuschagne's knock comes to an end. A crucial breakthrough by Dawid Malan.
Howout: c Ben Stokes b Dawid Malan

Commentary: Carey gets off the mark! Full and on off. Carey works it to long on for a single.
A sharp googly, around middle and off. Green goes back and defends it out safely.
Tossed up, on off. Green defends it out watchfully to the off side. A wicket and just 3 runs off it. A good over by Malan.
Tossed up, full and on off. Carey presses forward to defend it out.
On a length, sliding down leg. Carey leaves it alone.
FOUR! Up and over! Fuller and on off. Carey gets under it and lofts it towards long on. A couple of bounces and into the ropes.
Flatter, around off. Carey goes back and cuts it through point for a single.
Short and wide outside off. Green stands back and cuts it towards point for a single.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! Another one bites the dust! On a length, around off, turning in. Carey stays on the back foot and looks to cut it away to the off side. The ball takes the inside edge and goes onto the disturb the stumps behind. Australia lose their seventh wicket now. Mitchell Starc walks out to bat.
Howout: b Joe Root

Commentary: Touch short and on leg. Green pulls it through mid-wicket for a brace. Good running here.
Full and on off. Green defends it out.
Touch short and on middle. Green works it through square leg for a single now.
Short and outside off, Starc looks to chase it away but misses.
Flatter and short, outside off, Starc cuts it through point for a run.
Around off, Green helps it through square leg for a single.
Floated, on a length, wide of off. Green goes back and guides it through backward point. The batters take three before the fielder cuts it out.
Looped up, full and on off. Starc prods and defends it back to the bowler.
Full and on off. Starc defends it out.
Around off, defended out.
Short and outside off, Starc punches it towards point for a single.
Floated, full and on off. Green defends it out watchfully.
On off, Mitchell Starc heaves it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Loopy ball, outside off. Starc pushes it to covers for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Green defends it out.
On middle and leg, nudged on the leg side.

THREE BYES! Oh! That missed everything! Short and on middle, Cameron Green shuffles across and looks to pull but misses. Jos Buttler gets blinded by the batsman and fails to collect it as well. The ball goes over the stumps to fine leg for three byes.
Flatter, outside off. Starc pushes it to long off for a single.
Full and outside off. Mitchell Starc has a big swing at it. But only manages it to work it to mid on. He drops his bat down and holds his back. Looks like he has hurt himself.
On the pads, worked to mid-wicket for a single.
On middle and leg, Cameron Green works it to wide of long on for a brace.
Flatter, on middle. Green wrists it to mid-wicket for a single.
SIX! BANG! In the slot, outside off. Mitchell Starc clears his front leg and tonks it ove long on for a maximum.
On the pads, flicked to square leg for a run.
Fuller, outside off. Starc looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Tossed up, on middle. Starc slog-sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Short and on middle. This time Green does get bat on it as he pulls it to fine leg for three runs.
Slower through the air, on off. Starc drives it firmly to long off for a single.
Flatter, on leg. Green flicks it through mid-wicket for a run. Australia lead by 450 runs!
This is punched down to long off for a single.
Tossed up, fuller, outside off. Starc drives it through point for a brace.
On off, Starc cuts it to point.

OUT! CAUGHT! Loopy ball, on middle. Mitchell Starc takes the aerial route and heaves it towards deep mid-wicket. The ball goes high up in the air. Ollie Pope dives in front of him and pouches it with both hands. Joe Root has two wickets now and Mitchell Starc departs.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Joe Root

Commentary: On the pads, worked to wide of long on for a single.
This is flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Outside off, Cameron Green swipes this one to long on for a single.
Short and outside off. Cameron Green powers it down to long off for a couple of runs.
Very full, on the pads. Green flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Short and outside off. Jhye Richardson rocks back and hammers it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Cameron Green gets down on one knee and drags it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
SIX! What a shot! Right into the slot, on middle. Jhye Richardson gets low and slog-sweeps it over wide of long on for a biggie.

OUT! CAUGHT! Dawid Malan bags his second wicket. This was a tossed up delivery, on middle. Jhye Richardson gets down on one knee and again goes for the slog sweep. This time, it goes off the top edge and just ahead of the keeper on the leg side. Jos Buttler gulps it down easily. And with that, Australia have declared their innings on 230. They lead by 467 runs.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Dawid Malan

Commentary: Back of a length, outside off, nipping away. Burns shuffles across and shoulders his arms to it. A sigh of relief for Burns as this one is bowled wide.

An absolute beauty from Mitchell Starc! Good-length ball, around off, nips away a shade. Rory Burns gets across and looks to defend it out. The ball zips past the outside edge. It could've been curtain for Burns.
FOUR! Nicely played. Back of a length, sliding down leg. Burns comes across and helps it around the corner into the fence at fine leg.
BEATEN! Great bowling from Mitchell Starc! Angled in and seamed away. On a length, outside off, Burns gets beaten again as he looks to defend it out.
A good leave this time from Burns! Good-length, outside off. Burns shuffles across and shoulders his arms to it.
Awkward for Burns! Back of a length, outside off. Burns hangs his blade out. The ball takes the outer half and goes aerially towards gully but falls short. Burns survives a nasty over from Starc.
Good length and outside off. Hameed stays back and leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good-length delivery, outside off, nips in late. Hameed stays back and shoulders his arms.
On a length, wide outside off. Hameed has no stroke to offer this time either.
Close! Touch fuller, around off. The ball nips away off the deck. This time it is close to Hameed. He looks to defend it out but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Jhye Richardson makes Hameed play at it this time. A full-length, around off. Hameed prods and defends it out watchfully.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Yet again, England lose an early wicket. However, this time, you cannot fault the batsman much. This was just perfect, just perfect from Jhye Richardson. Hameed did everything possibly right that he could. It was landed on a length, outside off and Haseeb, rightfully, went forward to defend. But the ball just landed and kept on rising. Now, if that happens, no batsman in the world can control what is going to happen next. It would have been a bad shot had the outside edge been taken. That time, you could fault his technique. But here, the ball has climbed steeply, pinged the gloves and then gone to Alex Carey. So if you are Hameed, just nod your head to Jhye, admiring his delivery. Not your mistake at all. Tough, tough luck.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Jhye Richardson

Commentary: Short ball and outside off. Burns leaves it alone for the keeper.
Length ball, around middle. Burns gets inside the line and tucks it to the leg side.
Fuller, on the pads. Burns flicks it to square leg but straight to the fielder.
Back of a length, outside off. Burns leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good length, angled into the batter, on off. Burns shuffles across and defends it to point off the outer half.
Fuller and on leg. Burns clips it through mid-wicket. The batters take three runs comfortably before the fielder cuts it out in the deep.

Brilliant from Jhye Richardson! A full-length ball, angled across into the left-hander, around middle and leg. Burns stays back and looks to flick it away but misses. He gets pinged on the pads. Jhye Richardson puts in an appeal for an lbw but the umpire is unmoved.
Full, on leg again. Burns clips it to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! A flawless cover drive by Malan to kick-start his innings. A full-length ball, outside off. Malan leans in and creams it through cover for a boundary.
Great stop by Green! Back of a length, around off. Malan hangs his blade out. The ball goes off the outside edge to the right of gully. Green dives to his right and stops the ball well with one hand.

The crowd is backing the players here! A loud roar of out goes through the Adelaide Oval but the umpire is unmoved! Back of a length, around middle and leg. Malan hangs back and looks to defend it out but misses. The ball goes off his thigh pads towards gully. Green dives forward and takes a good catch. But no bat on it and Malan is still in the crease.
Back of a length, outside off, some extra bounce this time. Malan defends it towards gully awkwardly.
Short and on off. Burns stays back and punches it to point for a single.
That must've hurt! Good-length ball, around off, nips in off the deck. Malan hops and looks to defend it out but misses and gets pinged near the box. That is a nasty blow.
Good length, around off, nips in a touch again. Malan gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good length and outside off. Malan leaves it alone for the keeper.
BEAUTY! On a length, outside off., nips away a shade. Malan looks to defend it out but misses and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length and outside off, Malan leaves it alone watchfully.
Touch short, around middle and leg. Burns defends it out solidly.
Gets beaten this time! Length, around leg, angles across the left-hander. Burns looks to flicks it away but misses and gets hit on his thighs.
Good length, on off. Burns defends it out solidly.
Full length and on off. Burns drives it towards long off. They take three before the fielder cuts it out. It was a good looking shot from Burns.
Back of a length, outside off. Malan leaves it for the keeper.
Good length and outside off. Malan shoulders his arms to it.

Trouble, Trouble! A huge mix-up and a misfield helps the batters to get back to safety. A length ball, on the pads. Rory Burns flicks it to square leg. Malan wanted the single but Burns was not interested. The fielder charges towards the ball and looks to throw it at the non-striker's but he slips and goes down on the ground. This allows Malan to get back insde the crease.
Full and on the pads, Burns flicks it to short mid on.
FOUR! Up and over! Back of a length, wide outside off. Burns upper cuts it over gully and bags a boundary. This should help Burns with his confidence.
Good-length ball, around off. Rory Burns shoulders arms to that one.
Touch short, outside off. Burns get across to defend it out.
Fuller, on off. Burns comes across and defends it towards mid on. Burns is showing good signs here.
Dawid Malan trusting the bounce here. Good-length, outside off, nips in a long way but with some extra bounce this time. Malan shoulders his arms to it.
Back of a length, just outside off. Malan leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good length and wide outside off. Malan has not shot to offer.
Amazing work from Green! On a length, outside off. Malan guides it to the left of gully. Green dives to that side and makes a sharp stop.

A loud appeal for LBW but the umpire turns it down! Good length, outside off, this one nips back in sharply. Malan is stuck insde the crease and gets hit high on his pads, as he misses his defense. Jhye Richardson and the group behind the stumps appeal loudly but the umpire isn't interested. Steven Smith comes across and has a word with the bowler. A lot of details get exchanged in jusyt roughly 15 seconds and Smith does not take the review as the last the bowler says is it might to going above the stumps. The replays later confirm that the ball was going way over the stumps.
Length and on off, blocked out solidly. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4.
Tossed up, on middle. Rory Burns defends it out.
FOUR! Well played! Loopy ball, on middle. Rory Burns steps out and tucks it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary. Good use of the feet there by Burns.
That turned away sharply! Tossed up, turning away from middle. Rory Burns looks to defend off the back foot but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Rory Burns steps out and works it with spin to silly point.
Slower through the air, on off. Rory Burns presses forward to defend but the ball zips past the outside edge.
And once again, sharp turn there! Turns away from middle on off. Rory Burns looks to defend off the back foot but misses.
Length ball, on the pads. Malan pushes it to mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller in length, on off. Rory Burns looks to drive. The ball goes off the inner half to mid on.
Good-length ball, outside off. Rory Burns shoulders arms to that one.
Touch fuller, on middle. Rory Burns flicks it to deep square leg. Burns pushes for the second run and gets it comfortably. Good running!
Back of a length, on middle. Burns blocks it out from the crease.
Back of a length, on middle. Rory Burns defends it on the leg side.
Tossed up, on off. Dawid Malan looks to defend but the ball beats the outside edge.
On off, Malan guides it to backward point.
FOUR! Good shot! Loopy ball, outside off. Dawid Malan cuts it past point for a boundary.
Bounce and turn! Floated it up, outside off. The ball shoots up after hitting the deck. Dawid Malan looks to defend but misses.
On off, punched to point. Michael Neser misfields and allows a single.
On leg, Rory Burns tries to flick but gets hit on the pads.
Fuller, on off. Driven back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, around off. Dawid Malan looks to cut but misses. It was a lazy shot, Malan does not play it with venom. The ball zips past the inside edge and into the keeper's mitts.
Back of a length, on middle. Dawid Malan defends it back to the bowler.
On a length, on leg. Dawid Malan defends it out.
Beauty! Good-length ball, around off. Dawid Malan tries to cut it late but misses.
Short of a length, on off. Malan dabs it towards gully.
Tossed up, on off. Rory Burns looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad. The ball lobs up to the first slip fielder who catches it but it came off the back pad.
On off, Rory Burns looks to defend but gets beaten this time with the turn.
Loopy ball, on off. Burns defends it out.
Outside off, Rory Burns at first thinks to sweep but then leaves it alone.
Straighter this time, on off. Burns looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Fired in, around off. Rory Burns defends it off the back foot.
Good length, outside off, shaping away. Malan shoulders his arms to it.
A single now! Full-length ball, on off. Malan dig it out on the bounce towards mid off. The batters take a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Burns shoulders his arms at it.
On a length, around off, angled into the batter. Burns comes across and looks to flick it away but misses and gets rapped on high on the pads.
Good length and outside off. Burns defends it towards point.
EDGY! Burns gets lucky this time. Full length and on off. Burns looks to push it to the off side but inside-edges it towards fine leg and gets across for a single.
Flighted, full and on leg. Burns tucks it to short mid-wicket and scampers through for a single.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Malan works it to the left of mid on. Jhye Richardson gets low to his right and stops the ball.
Full and on off, pushed to the off side.
Around off, Malan defends it out.
Outside off, Malan stays back and leaves it alone.
Four! Nicely played. Short and outside off. Malan stays on the back foot and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Rory Burns defends it from the crease.
Fuller, on off. Burns pushes it to mid off.
Outside off, Burns lets it be.
Fuller and around off, Burns blocks it out.
Short of a length, on middle and leg. Rory Burns looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
On a good length, outside off. Burns lets it pass.
Tossed up, outside off. Malan leaves it alone.
Loopy ball, outside off. Dawid Malan lets it be.
Outside off, turning away. Malan leaves it untouched.
Short and outside off, quicker one. Malan looks to cut but misses.
Loopy ball, on middle. Malan defends it solidly.
A maiden! Fuller, on off. Played back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on middle. Burns turns it on the leg side.
FOUR! Cut away! Gets the width, outside off. Rory Burns pounces on it and cuts it through backward point to collect a boundary.
Good-length ball, outside off. Burns lets it sail through.
On a length, on off. Burns nudges it to mid on.
Back of a length, on off. Burns blocks it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Burns defends it out.
Flatter, fuller, on middle. Malan defends it out.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
Tossed up, on middle. Malan looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to backward point.
Full and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
On off, Malan presses forward to defend.
FOUR! A boundary to end the over! Outside off, Malan plays it late and cuts it past point for a boundary.
Fuller in length, on off. Burns pushes it to mid on.
Full again, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
Short of a length, on off. Burns taps it to point.
Good-length ball, outside off. Burns leaves it alone. It goes off the thigh pad and carries through to the keeper.
On middle, blocked out from the crease.
Back of a length, on off. Burns pushes it to covers.
Outside off, driven towards covers.
Tossed up, on middle. Dawid Malan looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to the first slip fielder.

DROPPED! Finally the edge comes, but Steven Smith drops it . Tossed up, on off. Dawid Malan looks to defend off the back foot. The ball goes off the outside edge to the first slip fielder. Steven Smith there spills down a dolly. The ball rolls behind him and the batters take a single.
Fuller and on off. Burns gets across and defends.
On off, Burns defends it out.
Beaten! Tossed up, on off. Rory Burns gets all squared up as he tries to defend. He misses and the ball zips past the outside edge.

OUT! LBW! Michael Neser you beauty! He gets the big wicket of Dawid Malan and Neser picks up his first wicket of the innings. This is the second time we are witnessing a reprieve not lasting long today. Earlier in the day, Smith was dropped once but did not last long after that, while Malan, who was just dropped by Smith an over before, falls on the next ball he faces. A length ball, around off, nips in sharply off the deck. Malan is stuck inside his crease and gets rapped on the pads. Neser appeals and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. Top class stuff from the bowler. Malan gives it a thought and takes the review eventually. The RTS shows no bat is involved. The Ball Tracker shows three reds and Malan has to walk back to the pavilion.
Howout: lbw b Michael Neser

Commentary: Outside off, left alone by Root.
Full and on off. Root defends it back to the bowler.
On a length, wide of off. Root leaves it alone for the keeper.
Fuller and on off. Root pushes it to cover and gets off the mark with a run.
Fuller and on off, Burns comes across and defends it out.
Floated, full and around middle, The ball turns away and bounces, going down leg. Root goes on his knees and looks to sweep it away but misses.

OH CLOSE! Tossed up, around middle. The ball turns down leg, with some extra bounce yet again. Root gets low and looks to sweep it away but misses. This time it looks like he gets some glove on it. Alex Carey moves to his left but could not gather the ball.
Flatter and outside off, the ball turns in sharply. Root goes back and works it to the leg side for a single.
On the pads, Burns clips it to square leg for a single.
Floated, on off. Root blocks it out solidly.
Full and on off. Root gets low and sweeps it towards square leg for a single.
Length and on off. Root defends it to the leg side.
Full and on the pads, Root clips it behind square for a brace.
Good length and outside off. Root looks to chase it but under-edges it to the slip cordon.
Full, around middle and leg. Root works it to mid on.
Fuller and on off. Root pushes it towards mid on.
Neser ends the over with a beauty! Good length and just outside off. Root looks to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside off.
Outside off, turning away. Burns leaves it alone.
Floated, outside off, some bounce off the deck. Burns leaves it alone.
EDGY! Tossed up, full and on off. Burns comes down the track and looks to flick it away. The ball goes off the outside edge towards mid on, but lands safely. The batters take a single.
LEG BYE! On the pads, Root misses his flick. The ball goes off the pads towards square leg. The batters take a le bye.
Looped up, on off, defended out solidly.
Outisde off, left alone by Burns.
Good length and on off, defended.
On off, Root stays back and pushes it towards cover for one.
Back of a length, on the shorter side, defended.
Shortish and on middle, this is nudged on the leg side.
Hits the length and on off, Burns blocks it solidly.

NOT OUT! That is why Burns reviewed! It hit the back leg and he survives. This is another good delivery from Green. Continues to land it on a length and outside off, this one jags back in. Burns goes back and tries to defend. It goes off something to the keeper who appeals after taking it. The finger is raised. Burns reviews straightaway. Replays show that the on-field call has to be overturned.
Flatter and down leg. Root helps it out with his pads.
Short and around off. Root stays back and defends it to point.
Around off, defended out.
Tossed up, full and on off. Root steps across and sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Floated, full and on off. Burns presses forward and defends it into the deck.
Quicker. Full and on middle. Burns defends it to the leg side.
FOUR! Nicely played. Short and outside off. Root stays back and punches it through backward point for a boundary.
Fuller, on off. Root defends it back to the bowler. Root is out of his crease and hence Green has a shy at the striker's end but misses.
Touch short, on off. Root guides it towards point and scampers through for a single.
Good length, outside off, nipping in. Burns shoulders his arms.
Back of a length, on the fourth stump line. Burns comes across and defends it out on the bounce to point.
Back of a length, outside off. Burns leaves it alone for the keeper.
On a length, on the fourth stump line. Root pushes it to the right of gully.
Fuller and outside off. Root step forward and blocks it out solidly.
On a length, outside off, the ball flies off the deck. Root has no stroke to offer.
Slightly short and outside off. Root gets across and defends it to point.
Good length, pitching outside off and shaping in. Root shuffles across and shoulders his arms at it.
Full length and on off. Root pushes his blade out and blocks it towards gully.
Length and around off. Burns looks to defend it out but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Back of a length, shaping in from outside off. Burns leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good length and outside off. Burns was caught in two minds, as he was looking to leave that one but in the end defends it onto the deck.
Full and on the pads. Burns misses his flick. The ball goes towards the keeper.
Full, around middle and leg. Burns clips it to the leg side.
A sharp bouncer, on off. Burns ducks under it and leaves it alone.
Length and on off. Root defends it solidly.
Fuller and on off. Root drives it past the mid off and gets three runs before the fielder cuts it out.
Outside off, left alone by Burns.
FOUR! EDGY! A full-length ball, on off. Burns looks to drive it through the cover region. The ball takes the outside edge and goes through gully and into the fence.
The ball flies off the deck! Back of a length, outside off. Burns looks to defend it out but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT! Steven Smith does not make any mistake this time. Jhye Richardson picks up his second wicket of the game and the Adelaide Oval erupts in joy. Full-length ball, around off, nips away a shade. Burns looks to defend it out but only manages to get an outside edge to slip cordon. Steven Smith keeps his eyes on the ball and takes a sharp catch low to his right. Ben Stokes will be the new man in.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Jhye Richardson

Commentary: Length and on off. Root blocks it out solidly.
BEATEN! Good length and outside off. Some extra bounce off the deck. Root looks to defend it out but gets beaten.
Good length, around off. Root defends it out.
Full length, just outside off. Root presses forward and blocks it out.
A sharp bouncer, outside off. Root ducks under it.
On a length, outside off. Root plays at it and pushes it towards gully.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Yet another delivery, on a length and outside off, not played at.
Another one on a length and outside off, Stokes lets it go to the keeper.
Easy leave yet again as this too is bowled outside off.
On off, Stokes hangs back and defends.
On the fuller side, Stokes lunges and tries to block but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Angled into the pads, Root works it through square leg for two.
On off, defended.
Angled into middle, Root works it to mid-wicket.
Outside off and on the shorter side. Left alone.
On middle, Root works it to mid on.
Another delivery, on a back of a length. Blocked well.
Outside off, Stokes lets it go to the keeper.

Not sure what Stokes was doing there! On middle, Stokes looks to defend, it goes off the outer half towards point. Stokes was busy admiring his stroke. Root was calling for a run, Stokes realized later and then completes it.
Back of a length and on off, Root stands tall and keeps it out.
On middle, Root works it towards mid on.
Drop and run! On off, Root plays it towards point and takes one.
A dot to end then! On middle, Stokes keeps it out.
Length and on off, Root defends.
Attacks the middle pole, Root stays rooted to his crease and plays it back to the bowler.
On middle, played back to the bowler.
Angling away from off, Root leaves it alone.
Good length and on off, Root plays it with soft hands towards point.
Yet another dot! On off, back of a length, Root gets on top of the bounce and plays it to point.
Loopy ball on middle, Stokes lunges and defends it out.
BEAUT! Slows it up, angles it in on off, this one lands and then turns away. Stokes is beaten as he tries to block.
On middle, kept out.
Flatter and on the stumps, Stokes goes back and puts bat on ball.
Lovely nut yet again! This lands on middle and then turns away. Stokes looks to defend but it goes more off the outer half on the off side.
A good ball to end by Lyon! Really good start from him. On middle, this also lands and spins away. Stokes hangs back to defend but it goes off the outer half through point for one.
Just outside off, Stokes shuffles across and leaves it alone.
A lot fuller than the last ball, Stokes still hangs back and defends.
Yet another one outside off, Stokes covers his off pole and shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length and on off, Stokes hangs back and plays it on the off side.
Slightly fuller and on middle, it is pushed to mid on.
On middle, kept out.
Good keeping! This lands on middle and then spins back down the leg side sharply. Root looks to flick but misses. Carey does well to move across and take it.
On middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
On middle, Stokes defends.
Slightly flatter, this one turns away. Stokes guides it to point for one.
Sharp turn again! This lands outside off and spins back in. Root goes back to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Again! Big turn! On off and spins back in. Root looks to play it on the leg side but no connection.
On middle, Stokes keeps it out well.
Half an appeal but turned down! Shorter and on the body, Stokes looks to nudged it on the leg side. There is a noise as the ball passes the batter. Carey takes it and appeals but turned down.
Cut him into half! That is a beauty! Length and outside off, this one jags back in. Stokes is cut into half as he tries to put bat on ball.
Shorter and on off, Stokes hops and keeps it out.
On middle, Stokes keeps it out.
That was close! An error of judgement from Stokes! This is angled into the pads, he thought it would slip down leg and hence, lets it go. He gets hit on the pads. Probably too high.
A single as this is worked with the turn through square leg.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
Solid again! On the stumps, kept out.
BEATEN! That is another beauty! Lyon has been excellent. On off, this one turns away. Stokes looks to defend but is beaten.
On the stumps this time, not a lot of turn. Kept out.
On the stumps, blocked.

That has hurt! OUCH! Root is in serious pain! Length and on middle, this one comes back in. Root looks to defend but gets an inside edge and it hits him near the crouch area. Root was hit in the abdomen this morning and could not take the field for a while. And now, he has been hit in an area where no physio or doctor can do anything, apart from give a few comforting words.
Good length and outside off again, left alone.
Angled into middle, Root looks to defend but it goes off the inner half on the leg side.

Well played! Fuller and on the pads, this is clipped through square leg for two. Smart bowling from Starc. By bringing in short leg, he planted the seed of a short ball in Joe Root's mind. But then, he went full. However, given the class of Root, he was up for it and played it well. He is still struggling to run between the wickets and that is something Australia will also notice.
NIcely drive! Fuller and outside off, Root drives it through covers for a couple more.
On middle, defended.
Floated, full and outside off. Stokes comes across and blocks it into the deck.
Short and outside off. Stokes goes back and blocks it out watchfully.
Looped up, around off. Stokes blocks it out.
Touch short and on off. Stokes defends it out without any hesitation.
Quicker and flatter, just outside off. Stokes defends it out on his back foot.
Flatter and on off. Stokes defends it out and sees off the penultimate over.
Length and on off, Root keeps it out.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! The way Steven Smith was jumping in joy after the catch was taken just shows how big and how pleased are the Aussies with this wicket. Exactly what they would have wanted before Stumps. Either the wicket of Root or Stokes, the former preferably and they have got it. Starc the provider again. Really have to feel sorry for Root. He was battling through a lot of pain, he just had the 4 balls to get through on Day 4 but he falls. He could have left this one alone though but probably the left-arm around angle does him in. This lands outside off, and holds its line. Root looks to defend, it was well outside off. He does so inside the line. The ball goes off the outside edge and the keeper does the rest. He walks back and so do the other plays as THAT IS STUMPS ON DAY 4!
Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Back of a length, on middle, angling in. Ollie Pope covers the line and blocks it out.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope leans and pushes it to point.
FOUR! Pope is off the mark! Fuller this time, on the pads. Ollie Pope clears his front leg and works it away through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope isn't troubled by that line and shoulders arms to it.
Tossed up, on off. Ben Stokes presses forward and blocks it out.
Floated ball, on middle. Ben Stokes defends it off the back foot.
Around off, Ben Stokes is solid in his defence.
Quicker one, on off. Ben Stokes looks to work it on the leg side off the back foot but misses. He gets hit above the knee roll. A mild appeal for an lbw but nothing from the umpire.
On leg, Stokes defends it on the leg side.
Loopy ball, on off. Stokes nudges it gently towards the off side. A maiden from Nathan Lyon.
Length ball, in the sixth stump channel. Ollie Pope lets it sail through.
Fuller, outside off. Ollie Pope shoulders arms.

OUT! TAKEN! Change of angle does the trick for Mitchell Starc! Goes over the wicket and bowls it on a good length, on off, angling away. Ollie Pope has a gentle poke at it. The ball goes off the outside edge and Steven Smith at second slip makes no mistake. Just the start Australia would have wanted. Second over of the day and Mitchell Starc removes Ollie Pope for a timid score. Half of the England side back in the hut now.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Touch fuller this time, Jos Buttler defends it towards the off side.
Good-length ball, around off. Jos Buttler leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Jos Buttler watches the ball and lets it go.
Full and on off, Ben Stokes lunges forward to block.
Loopy ball, on off. Ben Stokes defends it out off the back foot. Stokes has made up his mind that he is going to just block Lyon's deliveries.
This is defended off the back foot.
Outside off, spinning away. Ben Stokes is solid in his defence.
Tossed up, on middle. Blocked out.
Floated ball, on off. Stokes defends it from the crease.
Good-length ball, outside off, angling away. Jos Buttler looks to defend. The ball zips past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, angling away outside off, at 143.3 kph. Jos Buttler shoulders arms.
Attacks the stumps this time, Jos Buttler defends it to mid on.
On a good length, outside off, Jos Buttler offers no stroke.

FOUR! Oh dear! Jos Buttler is very fortunate there. Good-length ball, outside off, nipping away. Jos Buttler has a poke at it. The ball goes off the outside edge and flies towards the right of the keeper. Alex Carey though leaves it for David Warner at first slip to collect. But the ball passes between them and into the ropes. Should have been Alex Carey's catch.
Outside off, left alone.
Shortish, on middle. Ben Stokes works it through mid-wicket for a single.
Loopy ball, on off. Buttler tucks it on the leg side.
Tossed up, outside off. Jos Buttler looks to sweep. He gets hit on the arms and the ball lobs to the leg side.
This time Jos Buttler connects and sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.

Tossed up, full on off. Ben Stokes looks to defend. He misses and gets hit above the pads. The ball lobs off the pads to Marnus Labuschagne at silly point. Australia appeal for lbw but the umpire says no.
Fuller again. Ben Stokes defends it out.
On a length, onto the pads. Jos Buttler blocks it watchfully.
Full-length, outside off. Jos Buttler leaves that one alone.
Change of length this time, serves a shorter one, over middle. Jos Buttler ducks under it.
Good-length, on the pads, angling away a tad bit. Jos Buttler manages to get a slight outside edge towards second slip. The ball just fell short there.
Shortish, on the pads. Jos Buttler tucks it towards square leg. A single taken.
Back of a length, maintains the same line, on the pads. Ben Stokes pushes it to square leg for a single.
Outside off, flatter. Ben Stokes, on back foot, taps it towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Tosses it up, outside off, turning it away. Ben Stokes lets that go alone.
Flatter, quicker, outside off. Ben Stokes defends it out on backfoot.
Flatter again, outside off. Ben Stokes blocks it out.
Outside off. Ben Stokes, on backfoot, defends that one on the off side.
Shorter, outside off. Ben Stokes looks to defend that, but misses as the ball turns away a tad bit and gets rapped on the pads. Half an appeal by Australia, but the umpire is unmoved.
Outside off, angling across. Jos Buttler leaves that alone.
On a length, around middle. Jos Buttler blocks it solidly.
Good-length, outside off. Jos Buttler defends that one on the off side.
BEATEN! Serves a length ball, outside off. Jos Buttler looks to defend, but gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball nips away a tad bit.
Yorker length, on middle. Jos Buttler jams it back to the pitch.
Another yorker, around the off pole. Jos Buttler blocks it out.
Tossing it up, around the off pole. Ben Stokes leans forward and defends it out.
Loopy delivery, outside off. Ben Stokes lunges and blocks it solidly.
Flatter this time, outside off. Ben Stokes, on backfoot, defends it out.

OUT! LBW! Tossed up, on middle and leg. Ben Stokes looks to turn it away but misses. He gets rapped on the pads. Australia appeal for an lbw but the umpire says no. Steven Smith opts for a review. Nothing on UltraEdge. Ball Tracking shows all three reds. This is an excellent, excellent review by Australia. Steven Smith took his time before reviewing it but he will be a happy man now. Nathan Lyon bags his first wicket of this innings and what an important one. England needed Ben Stokes to stay at the middle but he has to walk back to the pavilion after doing all the blocking off Lyon's deliveries. Chris Woakes walks out to bat.
Howout: lbw b Nathan Lyon

RUN OUT MISSED! Oops, my dear - what happened there? Loopy delivery, on middle. Chris Woakes advanced down the pitch and looked to flick. But he missed and got hit on his pads. Now, Woakes was busy searching for the ball and was looking to his left. But the ball had rolled towards silly point. An alert Marcus Harris at silly point quickly collected the ball and had a shy at the striker's end, but he missed. Woakes was nowhere in the picture! This reminds me of an Ashes Test in Perth, 2006, at the WACA. Geraint Jones, the then keeper of England, had lunged to defend a delivery against Shane Warne. The ball went off his pads to Ricky Ponting at silly point and the entire Aussie contingent went up in an appeal for a bat-pad. But the ever-alert Ponting quickly threw the ball at the striker's end to catch Jones short and ran him out!
